      "id": "3i0w9npr",
      "title": "Multicamera Setup in Isaacsim for Fused Octomap in Moveit",
      "content": "## Multicamera Setup\n\n- Create a camera object from whichever view you want.\n- Use the Camera tool from the ROS2 Omnigraphs under Robotics under Tools for creating a graph for publishing camera views\n  - Select the camera prim associated with your camera object\n  - Change the frame ID to \"camera#\"\n  - Change the Node Namespace to \"camera#\"\n  - Enable all the modalities you would like to expose(especially point cloud for perception pipeline)\n- Once the camera graph is created, go to each modality section under the graph and enable \"useSystemTime\"\n- Finally, the most important but not stressed point is creating a static transform between the camera frame and the planning frame(world/baselink)\n  - You may use a ROS node outside of Isaacsim for this, or else\n  - Use the Ros2 Publish Transform Tree - This node in Isaac Sim can publish the pose of any sim prims to the ROS2 TF tree\n    - For fixed and one-time transforms, it is advisable to change the topic from tf to tf_static and enable the \"staticPublisher\" key\n\nThe above are the only steps to be done from the Isaacsim end.\n\nAt the configuration level:\n- Setup your sensor.yaml file as below\n```\n# config/sensors_3d.yaml\n# Global OctoMap resolution (meters/voxel)\noctomap_resolution: 0.02\n\n# Register both updaters (one per camera/topic)\nsensors:\n  - camera1_pointcloud\n  - camera2_pointcloud\n\n# --- Camera 1: uses /camera_1/points ---\ncamera1_pointcloud:\n  sensor_plugin: occupancy_map_monitor/PointCloudOctomapUpdater\n  point_cloud_topic: /camera_1/points\n  max_range: 5.0\n  point_subsample: 1\n  frame_subsample: 1\n  padding_offset: 0.1\n  padding_scale: 1.0\n  max_update_rate: 2.0\n  filtered_cloud_topic: /camera_1/filtered_points\n  # ns: cam1   # optional, helpful if you run many identical plugins\n\n  # Self-filter the robot links (edit to your robot; below is Panda as example)\n  self_filter:\n    self_mask:\n      self_see_links:\n        - panda_link0\n        - panda_link1\n        - panda_link2\n        - panda_link3\n        - panda_link4\n        - panda_link5\n        - panda_link6\n        - panda_link7\n        - panda_hand\n        - panda_leftfinger\n        - panda_rightfinger\n\n# --- Camera 2: uses /camera2/depth_pcl (already a PointCloud2) ---\ncamera2_pointcloud:\n  sensor_plugin: occupancy_map_monitor/PointCloudOctomapUpdater\n  point_cloud_topic: /camera2/depth_pcl\n  max_range: 5.0\n  point_subsample: 1\n  frame_subsample: 1\n  padding_offset: 0.1\n  padding_scale: 1.0\n  max_update_rate: 2.0\n  filtered_cloud_topic: /camera2/filtered_points\n  # ns: cam2   # optional\n\n  self_filter:\n    self_mask:\n      self_see_links:\n        - panda_link0\n        - panda_link1\n        - panda_link2\n        - panda_link3\n        - panda_link4\n        - panda_link5\n        - panda_link6\n        - panda_link7\n        - panda_hand\n        - panda_leftfinger\n        - panda_rightfinger\n```\n\n- The only other change made at launch file level is\n```\n   moveit_config = (\n        MoveItConfigsBuilder(\"panda\")\n        .robot_description(\n            file_path=\"config/panda.urdf.xacro\",\n            mappings={\n                \"ros2_control_hardware_type\": LaunchConfiguration(\"ros2_control_hardware_type\")\n            },\n        )\n        .robot_description_semantic(file_path=\"config/panda.srdf\")\n        .robot_description_kinematics(file_path=\"config/kinematics.yaml\")\n        .planning_scene_monitor(\n            publish_robot_description=True, publish_robot_description_semantic=True\n        )\n        .trajectory_execution(file_path=\"config/gripper_moveit_controllers.yaml\")\n        .planning_pipelines(pipelines=[\"ompl\"])\n        .sensors_3d(\n            file_path=os.path.join(\n                get_package_share_directory(\"perception_pipeline\"),\n                \"config/sensors_3d.yaml\",\n            )\n        )\n        .to_moveit_configs()\n    )\n```\n\n",
      "tags": [
        "multicamera",
        "octomap",
        "motionplanning",
        "obstacle"
      ],
