      "id": "4fj9uozs",
      "title": "2025-08-23 — Daily",
      "content": "# Top 3\n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n\n## Tasks\n\n### Tedx\n- How can we have better conversations?\n  - Understanding the type of conversations in each discussion is the key to be better at conversations.\n  - There are 3 different kinds of conversations:\n    - Practical\n    - Emotional\n    - Social\n  - Whenever someone comes to you asking for help, it is important to understand what kind of help they need, i.e, whether they want to be\n    - helped\n    - hugged\n    - heard\n  - The best way to understand what people want is by asking **Deep Questions**\n    - Deep questions are questions that would lead us to open up about our values, our beliefs, or our experiences.\n      - Instead of asking facts about someone's life, we should ask what they feel about their life.\n      - __Note__ When you hear vulnerability, we become vulnerable in return.\n---\n### Thinkschool:\n#### Anupam Mittal Podcast\n1. **What does he look for in a good team?**\n    - Evidence of exceptionalism in something - There should be some proxy for exceptionalism\n    - Business Acumen - It is not enough to make a great product, but to build a great business to be successful\n    - What is the non-obvious aspect of the business that someone has discovered?\n\n2. **How to develop business acumen?**\n    - Working in the finance sector early on\n    - Working as an investment banker\n\n3. What won't change?\n    - Travel business\n    - Cuisines\n    - Clothing - Digital natives would want variations\n\n*Note* \n-  Look for drivers that cultivate behaviours\n-  India is heavily underbranded\n-  Multipolar world - multiple countries become sources for aspiration\n-  Defence\n-  Institutions that are built in a democracy tend to stand the test of time for much longer\n-  Engage before educate\n-  Analysis Paralysis\n      \n\n\n\n\n## Journal\n\n## Wins\n",
