    {
      "id": "h80qg6ci",
      "title": "Control the UR5E+Robotiq using Moveit2 ROS2 in Isaacsim",
      "content": "## 🛠️ Transitioning the Repo Workflow to UR5e + Robotiq 85\n\n### ✅ Replication Status\n\nThe original repository workflow—designed for **UR10e + Robotiq 140 gripper** from https://github.com/qdeyna/ur10e_2f140_topic_based_ros2_control —was successfully replicated.\n\n---\n\n### 🔁 Validation on Custom Hardware (UR5e + Robotiq 85)\n\n- The only modification made was to update the **target prim values** in the **Articulation Controller nodes** inside the Action Graph of the provided USD file.\n- No other pipeline logic or code changes were required.\n- ✅ This minimal change was sufficient to validate that the same pipeline can be translated to the **UR5e + Robotiq 85 gripper** configuration.\n\n---\n\n### 🚀 Next Step: MoveIt Package Creation\n\nThe next step is to use **MoveIt Setup Assistant** to create a MoveIt package for the **UR5e + Robotiq 85** system.\n\n#### Key Components to Align:\n\n- `controller.yaml`:  \n  - Define controller names, interfaces, and a list of joints.\n  \n- `URDF`:  \n  - Merge the UR5e and Robotiq 85 gripper descriptions.\n  - Include correct transmissions and mimic joint relationships.\n  \n- `SRDF`:  \n  - Define planning groups (`manipulator`, `gripper`), end-effector, and collision settings.\n  \n- Joint Definitions:  \n  - Accurate joint limits (position, velocity, effort), safety margins, mimic rules for the Robotiq 85 gripper.\n\n---\n\n### ✅ Verification Checklist\n\n| Task | Status |\n|------|--------|\n| URDF correctly combines UR5e and Robotiq 85 gripper | ☑ |\n| SRDF defines planning groups and end-effector        | ☐ |\n| Joint limits and mimic behavior correctly set        | ☑ |\n| `controller.yaml` is configured and matches joint names | ☐ |\n| MoveIt demo launch confirms planning and execution   | ☐ |\n\n\n\n---\n\nOnce completed, the entire pipeline becomes compatible with the **UR5e + Robotiq 85** setup, enabling seamless planning and control.\n",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": "x58sfrwh",
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "note",
