    {
      "id": "ls831cxq",
      "title": "2025-08-25 — Daily",
      "content": "# Top 3\n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n\n## Tasks\n### <u>Tedx</u>\n<u> How to make learning as addictive as Social Media </u>\n- Freemium models - Another way to look at is as the rich paying for th education of the poor.\n- Streaks as an idea is what made the most difference in state of the art education platform.\n- Notification is the other idea that improved attendance because for an activity like eeducation people prefer to be educated.\n- Note: Its important to understand the content and timing of the notification also plays an important role in its effectiveness.\n\n<u> How to be happier according to science? </u>\n- Social Prediction Error : All the most often it feels like socializing will be awkward or tiring but research in general shows that the almost always feel happier after social interaction. Hence, before deciding not to participate in a social event, try to make it a point to step in there for 30 minutes and then see how it turns out later.\n- The Peak End Rule : The brain don't tend to remember all the experiences evenly.Rather, it remembers the most Intense movement, which is the peak and the ending.This means that even a bad day can be sandwiched if it ends on a high note. Hence end your day intensely on a good note.\n- Avoid \"Nutrasweet\" Connection : Social media is the neutrasweet version of connection. It reflects your brain into thinking, You are interacting, but it doesn't actually nourish you.\n- The Dopamine Rule : It's actually part of the Huberman's rule which says dopamine feels best when you earn it.If you constantly chase quick hits.By doing scrolling binch watching eating junk food.You train a brain to expect rewards without effort. stiff towarels effort based rewards - movements, learning or deep interactions.\n- The Gift & Curse of Hedonic Adaption : We quickly get used to both good and bad things.This is why achievements lose their excitement fast.But also why pain feeds over time. Hence, try to save the good Violet last pause and appreciate small joints before they fade into the background and when life gets hard, Remind yourself you will adjust.\n- Start a Delight Practise : Graduate is great, but sometimes can feel forced. Hence, it's always better to do something called as a Delight Practice where you train yourself to notice tiny moments of joy in real-time. Make it a point to notice at least one thing that made me smile every day.\n- Adults need to play too : Unstructured joyful activities with no productivity goal per se reset your brain in ways nothing else can.\n\n\n## Journal\n\n\n## Wins\n",
      "tags": [
        "happiness",
        "todo"
      ],
      "projectId": null,
