      "id": "pkg90ymq",
      "title": "Pick and Place using UR5E + Robotiq",
      "content": "Pre-Tasks:\n1. Follow the perception pipeline integration with IsaacSim\n  - Complete the work for Panda Robot\n  - Test the hypothesis that \"as long as the target is visible in the camera, it can be included in the planning scene\"\n2. Test if multiple cameras can be used to serve the perception pipeline \n\n\n### Action Steps:\n1. Use Robotiq + UR5E to do pick and place with the Carbody Spawned.\n2. Use and activate the perception pipeline\n     - Use a Multicamera setup to build a workspace and planning scene.\n3. Perform reachability analysis\n4. Perform workspace analysis - https://moveit.ai/assets/pdfs/2013/icra2013tutorial/ICRATutorial-Workspace.pdf\n\nRefer https://github.com/pietrolechthaler/UR5-Pick-and-Place-Simulation/blob/main/catkin_ws/src/motion_planning/scripts/motion_planning.py for pick and place logic in ros1(port the same to ros2)",
