    {
      "id": "xgv0q61j",
      "title": "Control the robot in Isaac Sim with Python with a PD Controller",
      "content": "# `ur5e_robotiq_speed_control_with_position.py` — Detailed Explanation\n\n> **Goal:** Smoothly move **one** gripper joint in Isaac Sim (the Robotiq 85 “driver” joint) with a **speed limit**—either to a fixed target or by **oscillating** between open/close bounds.  \n> **Why it’s useful:** This script demonstrates a reusable “rate-limited position controller” pattern. You can adapt it to any joint or robot configuration in Isaac Sim.\n\n---\n\n## What this script does\n\n1. **Starts Isaac Sim** and loads your robot USD file at the given prim path.  \n2. **Finds the gripper’s driver joint** by name, resolves its index, and prepares to control it.  \n3. **Every simulation step**, computes a new **target joint position** using a **rate limiter** (max speed per second).  \n4. **Writes the target** to the joint drive so PhysX moves it smoothly.  \n5. Supports two behaviors:\n   - **Hold mode**: move to a fixed target (`--target`) and hold it.  \n   - **Oscillate mode**: bounce between `--open-pos` and `--close-pos` at chosen speeds.\n\n---\n\n## Quick start\n\n```bash\n# Oscillate between open/close at 0.05 units/sec (default both ways)\npython ur5e_robotiq_speed_control_with_position.py --usd /path/to/ur5e_robotiq_flattened.usd --prim /World/ur\n\n# Move to target (e.g., 0.6) and hold, with global speed cap 0.08\npython ur5e_robotiq_speed_control_with_position.py --target 0.6 --speed 0.08\n\n# Asymmetric speeds: open slower (0.04), close faster (0.10)\npython ur5e_robotiq_speed_control_with_position.py --speed-open 0.04 --speed-close 0.10\n```\n\n\n```python\n\n# ur5e_robotiq_speed_control_with_position.py\nfrom isaacsim import SimulationApp\nsimulation_app = SimulationApp({\"headless\": False})\n\n# ---- Cross-version imports ----\ntry:\n    from isaacsim.core.api import World\n    from isaacsim.core.articulations import ArticulationView\n    from isaacsim.core.utils.types import ArticulationAction\n    from isaacsim.core.utils.stage import add_reference_to_stage\nexcept Exception:\n    from omni.isaac.core import World\n    from omni.isaac.core.articulations import ArticulationView\n    from omni.isaac.core.utils.types import ArticulationAction\n    from omni.isaac.core.utils.stage import add_reference_to_stage\n\nimport argparse, numpy as np\n\n# Defaults (can be overridden via CLI)\nROBOT_USD       = \"/data/tvp_ws/nvidia_stack/tvp_nv_tests/ur5e_robotiq_flattened.usd\"\nROBOT_PRIM_PATH = \"/World/ur\"\nDRIVER_JOINT    = \"robotiq_85_left_knuckle_joint\"\nOPEN_POS, CLOSE_POS = 0.00, 0.80\n\n# ---- CLI ----\np = argparse.ArgumentParser(\"Speed controlled single-joint gripper\")\np.add_argument(\"--usd\", default=ROBOT_USD)\np.add_argument(\"--prim\", default=ROBOT_PRIM_PATH)\np.add_argument(\"--joint\", default=DRIVER_JOINT)\np.add_argument(\"--open-pos\", type=float, default=OPEN_POS)\np.add_argument(\"--close-pos\", type=float, default=CLOSE_POS)\np.add_argument(\"--target\", type=float, default=None, help=\"If set, move to this value and hold.\")\np.add_argument(\"--speed\", type=float, default=None, help=\"Max joint speed (units/sec) for both directions.\")\np.add_argument(\"--speed-open\", type=float, default=0.05, help=\"Speed when moving toward OPEN_POS (units/sec).\")\np.add_argument(\"--speed-close\", type=float, default=0.05, help=\"Speed when moving toward CLOSE_POS (units/sec).\")\nargs = p.parse_args()\n\n# Unify speed arguments\nif args.speed is not None:\n    args.speed_open = args.speed_close = float(args.speed)\n\n# ---- World + robot ----\nworld = World(stage_units_in_meters=1.0)\nadd_reference_to_stage(usd_path=args.usd, prim_path=args.prim)\nview = ArticulationView(prim_paths_expr=args.prim, name=\"ur_view\")\nworld.scene.add(view)\ntry:\n    world.scene.add_default_ground_plane()\nexcept Exception:\n    try: world.add_default_ground_plane()\n    except Exception: pass\nworld.reset()\n\n# ---- Helpers ----\ndef get_dt_compat(w):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns the physics timestep (dt) for the simulation world, using a compatible method for different Isaac Sim versions.\n    Tries several possible method names, returns a default of 1/60 if none found.\n    \"\"\"\n    for name in (\"get_physics_dt\", \"get_simulation_dt\", \"get_physics_time_step\"):\n        f = getattr(w, name, None)\n        if f:\n            try:\n                return float(f())\n            except Exception:\n                pass\n    return 1.0/60.0  # safe fallback\n\ndef get_dof_names_compat(v):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns a list of DOF (joint) names for the given articulation view, compatible with multiple Isaac Sim versions.\n    Tries several possible attributes and methods to retrieve the names.\n    \"\"\"\n    if hasattr(v, \"get_dof_names\"):\n        try:\n            n = v.get_dof_names()\n            if n: return list(n)\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n    for attr in (\"dof_names\", \"_dof_names\"):\n        if hasattr(v, attr):\n            try: return list(getattr(v, attr))\n            except Exception: pass\n    av = getattr(v, \"_articulation_view\", None)\n    if av and hasattr(av, \"get_dof_names\"):\n        try:\n            n = av.get_dof_names()\n            if n: return list(n)\n        except Exception: pass\n    return []\n\ndef read_all_positions_compat(v):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns the current joint positions for the given articulation view, compatible with multiple Isaac Sim versions.\n    Tries several possible method names to retrieve the positions as a numpy array.\n    \"\"\"\n    for reader in (\"get_joint_positions\", \"get_joints_positions\"):\n        fn = getattr(v, reader, None)\n        if fn:\n            try:\n                q = np.array(fn(), dtype=float)\n                if q.ndim == 2: q = q[0]\n                return q\n            except Exception: pass\n    return None\n\ndef set_single_joint(v, idx, value, joint_names=None):\n    \"\"\"\n    Sets the position of a single joint (by index) in the articulation view to the specified value.\n    Tries several compatible APIs for different Isaac Sim versions. Falls back to setting the full joint vector if needed.\n    Optionally prints the joint name and value set.\n    \"\"\"\n    one = np.array([float(value)], dtype=float)\n    idxs = np.array([int(idx)], dtype=np.int32)\n\n    for fn_name, kw_idxs in [\n        (\"set_joint_positions\", \"joint_indices\"),\n        (\"set_joint_positions\", \"indices\"),\n        (\"set_joints_positions\", \"joint_indices\"),\n        (\"set_joints_positions\", \"indices\"),\n    ]:\n        fn = getattr(v, fn_name, None)\n        if fn:\n            try:\n                fn(one, **{kw_idxs: idxs})\n                jname = joint_names[idx] if joint_names else f\"idx{idx}\"\n                print(f\"[cmd] {jname} := {float(value):.4f}\")\n                return\n            except TypeError: pass\n            except Exception: pass\n\n    q = read_all_positions_compat(v)\n    if q is None:\n        raise RuntimeError(\"No compatible joint setter and cannot read positions.\")\n    q[idx] = float(value)\n    try:\n        v.apply_action(ArticulationAction(joint_positions=q.tolist()))\n        print(f\"[cmd/full] set vector, {joint_names[idx] if joint_names else idx}={value:.4f}\")\n        return\n    except Exception: pass\n    for fn_name in (\"set_joint_positions\", \"set_joints_positions\"):\n        fn = getattr(v, fn_name, None)\n        if fn:\n            try:\n                fn(q.tolist()); print(f\"[cmd/full] set vector2, idx{idx}={value:.4f}\"); return\n            except Exception: pass\n    raise RuntimeError(\"Could not set joint position with any known API.\")\n\ndef clamp(x, lo, hi):\n    \"\"\"\n    Clamps the value x to the range [lo, hi].\n    \"\"\"\n    return max(lo, min(hi, x))\n\ndef move_towards(curr, goal, v_max, dt):\n    \"\"\"\n    Moves the current value towards the goal at a maximum rate of v_max per second (scaled by dt).\n    Returns the new value and a boolean indicating if the goal was reached (within tolerance).\n    \"\"\"\n    if curr == goal: return curr, True\n    step = v_max * dt\n    if goal > curr:\n        nxt = min(curr + step, goal)\n    else:\n        nxt = max(curr - step, goal)\n    return nxt, abs(nxt - goal) < 1e-5\n\n# ---- Resolve joint ----\nnames = get_dof_names_compat(view)\nif not names:\n    for _ in range(3): world.step(render=True)\n    names = get_dof_names_compat(view)\nif not names: raise RuntimeError(\"Failed to get DOF names; check USD/prim.\")\n\nname_to_idx = {n: i for i, n in enumerate(names)}\nif args.joint not in name_to_idx:\n    raise RuntimeError(f\"Joint '{args.joint}' not found. Available:\\n{names}\")\nJ = name_to_idx[args.joint]\nprint(f\"[ur] Controlling joint '{args.joint}' (index {J})\")\n\nOPEN_POS = float(args.open_pos); CLOSE_POS = float(args.close_pos)\ndt = get_dt_compat(world)\n\n# Determine mode\nhold_goal = None\nif args.target is not None:\n    hold_goal = clamp(float(args.target), OPEN_POS, CLOSE_POS)\nmode = \"hold\" if hold_goal is not None else \"oscillate\"\nprint(f\"[mode] {mode} | dt={dt:.4f}s | v_open={args.speed_open:.4f} u/s | v_close={args.speed_close:.4f} u/s\")\n\n# Init target\nq0 = read_all_positions_compat(view)\ntarget = float(q0[J]) if q0 is not None else OPEN_POS\nosc_goal = CLOSE_POS if target <= (OPEN_POS + CLOSE_POS)/2.0 else OPEN_POS  # start heading somewhere sensible\n\n# ---- Main loop ----\nreset_needed = False\nwhile simulation_app.is_running():\n    world.step(render=True)\n\n    if world.is_stopped() and not reset_needed:\n        reset_needed = True\n\n    if world.is_playing():\n        if reset_needed:\n            world.reset()\n            reset_needed = False\n\n        if mode == \"hold\":\n            v = args.speed_close if hold_goal > target else args.speed_open\n            target, _ = move_towards(target, hold_goal, v, dt)\n\n        else:  # oscillate between bounds with asymmetric speeds\n            v = args.speed_close if osc_goal > target else args.speed_open\n            target, done = move_towards(target, osc_goal, v, dt)\n            if done:\n                osc_goal = OPEN_POS if osc_goal == CLOSE_POS else CLOSE_POS  # flip at ends\n\n        set_single_joint(view, J, clamp(target, OPEN_POS, CLOSE_POS), joint_names=names)\n\nsimulation_app.close()\n\n",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": "x58sfrwh",
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "note",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2025-08-27T00:36:30.062Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-08-27T00:41:15.191Z",
      "attachments": [],
      "links": [],
      "deletedAt": null
    },
