    {
      "id": "cenumrb0",
      "title": "Gello/Dynamixel Setup",
      "content": "# UR5e + Dynamixel Teleop: Debug Logbook & Playbook\n\nA compact, “pull-it-off-the-shelf” reference of what broke, why, how we fixed it, and the exact commands we used. This is meant to be reusable for future bring-ups and interviews.\n\n---\n\n## 1) System Overview (mental model)\n\n```\n[Gello/DXL arm] --(TTL bus via FTDI)--> [Linux USB-serial] --> [dynamixel_workbench_controllers]\n                                           | publishes /dynamixel_workbench/joint_states @ 100–200 Hz\n\n   [Your mapper node]\n     /joint_states  ->  mapping + smoothing ->  /scaled_pos_joint_traj_controller/command (UR5e)\n                                             (single-point trajectories, future-dated)\n```\n\nKey: Dynamixel rate controls **input freshness**; UR responsiveness depends on **valid, future-dated** command streaming (60–120 Hz, look-ahead \\~100–200 ms).\n\n---\n\n## 2) Challenges → Root Causes → Fixes\n\n### A) Low `/joint_states` rate (\\~23–30 Hz)\n\n* **Why:** Slow bus (57.6 kbps), reply delays, and extra ACKs.\n* **Fixes:**\n\n  * **EEPROM** (one-time):\n\n    * `Baud_Rate = 3` (1 Mbps)\n    * `Return_Delay_Time = 0`\n    * `Status_Return_Level = 1` (or `2` if you **need** WRITE ACKs; `1` is faster)\n  * **Driver periods:** `publish_period = dxl_read_period = dxl_write_period = 0.010 → ~100 Hz` (or `0.005 → ~200 Hz`)\n  * **USB latency (optional):** set to 1 ms *only if stable on your system*.\n\n**Commands we used**\n\n```bash\n# Program EEPROM (scan then set), using the stable by-id path:\npython dxl_scan_and_set.py \\\n  --port /dev/serial/by-id/usb-FTDI_USB__-__Serial_Converter_FT9HD7RD-if00-port0 \\\n  --target-baud 1000000 --srl 1 --rdt 0\n# Verify\npython dxl_status_check.py\n```\n\n---\n\n### B) “Faster publish feels less reactive” / micro-hesitations\n\n* **Why:** Streaming single-point trajectories **without future-dating** → messages arrive “in the past”; controller retimes/drops them.\n* **Fix:** **Future-date** each point:\n\n  * `traj.header.stamp = now + lookahead`\n  * `pt.time_from_start = lookahead`\n  * **lookahead** ≈ 0.10–0.20 s; **command\\_hz** ≈ 60–120 Hz (≤ UR’s \\~125 Hz loop)\n\n**Pattern we adopted (snippet)**\n\n```python\nself.command_hz = 100.0\nself.lookahead  = 0.12     # 120 ms\nself.cmd_timer  = rospy.Timer(rospy.Duration(1.0/self.command_hz), self._tick)\n\ndef _tick(self, _):\n    if self.latest is None: return\n    L = rospy.Duration.from_sec(self.lookahead)\n    now = rospy.Time.now()\n\n    traj = JointTrajectory()\n    traj.joint_names  = JOINT_NAMES[:-1]\n    traj.header.stamp = now + L\n\n    pt = JointTrajectoryPoint()\n    pt.positions       = self.latest[:-1]\n    pt.time_from_start = L\n\n    traj.points = [pt]\n    self.pub.publish(traj)\n\n    # Gripper slower (10–30 Hz) and change-driven\n    self.gripper_controller(self.latest[-1])\n```\n\n---\n\n### C) Node crashes when adding EEPROM keys in `basic.yaml`\n\n* **Symptoms:**\n\n  ```\n  Failed to write value[0] on items[Return_Delay_Time]...\n  ```\n* **Why:** `dynamixel_workbench_controllers` tries to **write** any extra keys on startup; EEPROM writes are timing-sensitive and unnecessary (we already set via script).\n* **Fix:** Keep runtime YAML **minimal**: **IDs only** + top-level `items:` for cyclic reads.\n\n**Safe YAML**\n\n```yaml\njoint_1: { ID: 1 }\njoint_2: { ID: 2 }\njoint_3: { ID: 3 }\njoint_4: { ID: 4 }\njoint_5: { ID: 5 }\njoint_6: { ID: 6 }\ngripper: { ID: 7 }\n\nitems:\n  - Present_Position\n```\n\n---\n\n### D) `YAML::InvalidNode`\n\n* **Why:** Structural issue (tabs, CRLF/BOM, `items:` without a list, or edited wrong file).\n* **Fix:** Use IDs-only YAML; validate formatting.\n\n**Checks**\n\n```bash\ngrep -nP '\\t' path/basic.yaml || echo \"no tabs ✓\"\ndos2unix path/basic.yaml\npython - <<'PY'\nimport yaml; print(\"TOP:\", list(yaml.safe_load(open(\"path/basic.yaml\")).keys()))\nPY\n```\n\n---\n\n### E) “Failed to open port!” (serial) / suddenly stops working\n\n* **Why:**\n\n  * **Container device mismatch:** device renumbered (ttyUSB0→1) but container mapped only the old one.\n  * Port **busy** (other Python/ROS process holding `/dev/ttyUSBx`).\n  * Using a **stale by-id** symlink **inside** Docker.\n* **Fixes:**\n\n  * Free the port; use **correct device** **in this shell**; or **restart container** with stable mapping.\n\n**Busy port detection / free**\n\n```bash\nlsof /dev/ttyUSB0\nlsof -t /dev/ttyUSB0 | xargs -r kill -TERM\nsleep 1\nlsof -t /dev/ttyUSB0 | xargs -r kill -KILL\n```\n\n**Find actual port**\n\n```bash\nls -l /dev/serial/by-id/\nls -l /dev/ttyUSB*\ndmesg | tail -n 50 | grep -i ttyUSB   # e.g., “now attached to ttyUSB1”\n```\n\n**SDK sanity (open test)**\n\n```bash\npython - <<'PY'\nfrom dynamixel_sdk import *\nfor dev in [\"/dev/ttyUSB0\",\"/dev/ttyUSB1\",\n            \"/dev/serial/by-id/usb-FTDI_USB__-__Serial_Converter_FT9HD7RD-if00-port0\"]:\n    try:\n        p=PortHandler(dev); ok=p.openPort()\n        ok2=p.setBaudRate(1000000) if ok else False\n        print(dev,\"open:\",ok,\"baud1M:\",ok2)\n        if ok: p.closePort()\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(dev,\"ERR:\",e)\nPY\n```\n\n**Docker (robust)**\n\n* **Best:** map stable by-id to `/dev/dxl` and always use that:\n\n  ```bash\n  docker run --rm -it \\\n    --device=/dev/serial/by-id/usb-FTDI_USB__-__Serial_Converter_FT9HD7RD-if00-port0:/dev/dxl \\\n    --group-add dialout your_image\n  # Inside: roslaunch ... usb_port:=/dev/dxl dxl_baud_rate:=1000000\n  ```\n\n* **Alternative:** allow hot-plug without restarts:\n\n  ```bash\n  docker run -it --rm -v /dev:/dev --device-cgroup-rule='c 188:* rwm' --group-add dialout your_image\n  ```\n\n* **Host udev symlink (most bulletproof):**\n\n  ```bash\n  # Create /dev/dxl for this exact FTDI serial\n  sudo tee /etc/udev/rules.d/99-dxl-ft232h.rules >/dev/null <<'RULE'\n  ACTION==\"add\", SUBSYSTEM==\"tty\", ATTRS{idVendor}==\"0403\", ATTRS{idProduct}==\"6014\", ATTRS{serial}==\"FT9HD7RD\", SYMLINK+=\"dxl\"\n  RULE\n  sudo udevadm control --reload-rules && sudo udevadm trigger\n  # docker run --device=/dev/dxl:/dev/dxl ...\n  ```\n\n---\n\n### F) Gripper update rate\n\n* **Why:** Path is slower (socket/Modbus + mechanics). High rates don’t help; can spam the bus.\n* **Fix:** Drive gripper at **10–30 Hz**, change-driven with deadband.\n\n---\n\n## 3) Final Working Settings (stable baseline)\n\n* **DXL bus**\n  EEPROM: `Baud=1 Mbps`, `RDT=0`, `SRL=1 (or 2 if you need write ACKs)`\n  Launch: `publish/read/write period = 0.010` (100 Hz) or `0.005` (200 Hz)\n\n* **Mapper → UR**\n  `command_hz = 100–120`\n  `lookahead  = 0.12–0.20 s`\n  single-point trajectories, leave velocities unset, `queue_size=1`\n  gripper: 10–30 Hz, change-driven\n\n* **YAML**\n  IDs only + `items: [Present_Position]`\n\n* **Docker**\n  Map stable device (`/dev/dxl`) or bind `/dev` with cgroup rule; always use the mapped path in `usb_port`.\n\n---\n\n## 4) Frequently Used Commands (copy/paste ready)\n\n**Check ports & who holds them**\n\n```bash\nls -l /dev/serial/by-id/ ; ls -l /dev/ttyUSB*\ndmesg | tail -n 50 | grep -i ttyUSB\nlsof /dev/ttyUSB0\n```\n\n**Free a port**\n\n```bash\nlsof -t /dev/ttyUSB0 | xargs -r kill -TERM\nsleep 1\nlsof -t /dev/ttyUSB0 | xargs -r kill -KILL\n```\n\n**Verify EEPROM (all IDs)**\n\n```bash\npython dxl_status_check.py\n# Expect: Baud=3, RDT=0, SRL=1 or 2\n```\n\n**Set EEPROM (example: 1 Mbps, SRL=1, RDT=0)**\n\n```bash\npython dxl_scan_and_set.py --port /dev/serial/by-id/usb-FTDI_USB__-__Serial_Converter_FT9HD7RD-if00-port0 \\\n  --target-baud 1000000 --srl 1 --rdt 0\n```\n\n**Launch workbench (match EEPROM baud)**\n\n```bash\nroslaunch dynamixel_workbench_controllers dynamixel_controllers.launch \\\n  usb_port:=/dev/dxl dxl_baud_rate:=1000000\n```\n\n**ROS topic rate**\n\n```bash\nrostopic hz /dynamixel_workbench/joint_states\n```\n\n**Clean big ROS logs**\n\n```bash\nrosclean purge -y\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5) Troubleshooting Matrix\n\n| Symptom                    | Likely Cause                                 | What to Run / Do                                               |                                                                           |\n| -------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| `Failed to open the port!` | Wrong `/dev/ttyUSBx` in container; port busy | `ls -l /dev/ttyUSB*`, \\`dmesg                                  | grep ttyUSB`, `lsof /dev/ttyUSBx\\`; remap device into Docker or free port |\n| `YAML::InvalidNode`        | `items:` wrong level/list, tabs, CRLF/BOM    | IDs-only YAML; `dos2unix`, check with `yaml.safe_load`         |                                                                           |\n| Low Hz (\\~23–30)           | Baud low, delays, extra ACKs                 | EEPROM set: `Baud=1M`, `RDT=0`, `SRL=1`; periods 0.010/0.005   |                                                                           |\n| High publish feels worse   | Past-point drops                             | Future-date points; `lookahead=0.12–0.20`, `command_hz=60–120` |                                                                           |\n| Node crashes on start      | YAML trying to write EEPROM                  | Remove EEPROM keys from YAML; set via script once              |                                                                           |\n| Gripper lags               | Over-publishing / low BW path                | 10–30 Hz, change-driven; deadband                              |                                                                           |\n\n---\n\n## 6) Reusable Artifacts (what to package)\n\n* `scripts/`\n\n  * `dxl_scan_and_set.py` (CLI: `--port`, `--srl`, `--rdt`, `--target-baud`, `--verify-only`)\n  * `dxl_status_check.py`\n  * `free_dxl.sh` (kill any process holding the device)\n* `config/`\n\n  * `dxl_ids.yaml` (IDs only)\n  * `dxl_ids_pos.yaml` (IDs + `Present_Position`)\n* `compose.yaml` (maps `/dev/dxl` → container; adds `dialout` group)\n* `README.md`\n\n  * “Why look-ahead matters”\n  * “DXL throughput math & EEPROM meanings”\n  * “Docker device mapping patterns”\n  * Troubleshooting matrix (above)\n\n---\n\n## 7) Interview-ready Takeaways (1–2 liners)\n\n* **Throughput & latency:** “We moved the DXL bus from 57.6 kbps to 1 Mbps, disabled return delays, and avoided write ACKs (SRL=1) to lift `/joint_states` from \\~23 Hz to \\~100–200 Hz.”\n* **Controller semantics:** “UR’s interface is time-based; streaming points must be **future-dated**. With a 100–200 ms look-ahead and 60–120 Hz, points never arrive in the past, so motion becomes more responsive as we publish faster.”\n* **Runtime vs provisioning:** “EEPROM is provisioned once with an SDK script; runtime YAML stays minimal to avoid brittle startup writes.”\n* **Containerization:** “Device renumbering (ttyUSB0↔1) breaks containers unless you pass a **stable device** (`/dev/dxl` via udev) or allow hot-plug (`-v /dev:/dev` + cgroup rule).”\n",
