    {
      "id": "vzidu1so",
      "title": "Moveit Setup Assistant Debugging",
      "content": "### MSA Crash Loading URDF — Postmortem\n\n**Issue**  \nMSA segfaults (exit code –11) when loading URDF, after robot model loaded, inside embedded RViz panel.\n\n**Root cause**  \nRegression in newer Humble builds — hidden bug in embedded RViz’s `PropertyTreeModel::propertyHiddenChanged` triggered by certain URDF structures.\n\n**Evidence**  \n- Xacro → URDF and `check_urdf` passed.  \n- Standalone RViz works.  \n- Crashes only with current MSA/RViz versions; same URDF works on older build.  \n- Open GitHub issue in MoveIt2 for “crashes when uploading URDF” in Humble. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}  \n\n**Resolution / Workarounds**  \n1. Run MSA in Docker / container pinned to older stable builds.  \n2. Copy older `.deb` files from working machine and install/hold.  \n3. Use non-GUI config generation (via `moveit_configs_utils`) to avoid the crash.  \n4. In URDF, gate complex parts (camera, helpers) to simplify the model for loading in MSA.\n\n**Notes / caveats**  \n- Because older versions are often removed from ROS package mirrors, pin installs may not always be possible.  \n- The bug is in GUI interaction, so headless or background tools are less affected.  \n- Keep this doc with your robotics stack repository so future regressions are traceable.\n",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": "y9081w3r",
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "note",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2025-10-01T03:58:46.714Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-10-01T03:58:46.714Z",
      "attachments": [],
      "links": [],
      "deletedAt": null
    },
