    {
      "id": "h5qbq28h",
      "title": "Notebook LM Insights",
      "content": "Skill Deconstruction prompt for Video Generation\nPlease focus on: 1) Deconstructing these skills into the smallest, most manageable, and\nlearnable units. 2) Selecting which of these are most critical to a professional final video, using the 80/20 rule. 3) Establishing the most effective and logical order in which to learn the selected building blocks. 4) compressing, summarizing, and simplifying the most important 20% of this material into its most basic form. 5) encode this information into easy-to-remember acronyms or metaphors.\n\nSource Attribution for Credibility\nInstant Expert Positioning: Use citations to back up your content with authoritative sources\nDiscovery Prompt (General Search): \"Find peer-reviewed studies. industry reports, and expert opinions on [your topic] from the last 2 year\nAnalysis Prompt: \"Which sources would add the most credibility to my argument about [specific claim]?\"\nAdditional Note: Ask \"Generate a list of quotable statistics with proper attribution for my article about ſtopicl\"\n\nProposal Power-Ups: Include source attributions in client proposals to demonstrate research depth\nDiscovery Prompt (General Search): \"Find case studies and ROI data about [solution you're proposing] from reputable sources\"\nAnalysis Prompt: \"Which data points and sources would be most compelling for a [client industry] executive making a buying decision?\"\n\n\nCourse Material Validation: Ensure your educational content is properly sourced and credible\nDiscovery Prompt (Internal Drive): \"Find all my course materials, teaching notes, and reference documents.\"\nDiscovery Prompt (General Search): \"Find academic papers and authoritative sources that support the concepts in my course.\"\nAnalysis Prompt: \"Identify any claims in my course that lack proper citation and suggest authoritative sources to support them.\"\n\n\n\nDiscovery Prompt (Internal Drive): \"Find my service descriptions, onboarding documents, FAQs and client success stories\"\nAnalysis Prompt: \"Create a warm, conversational video that explains my services and sets expectations for our work together\"\nDissemination: Use \"Host Instructions\" to create different versions - formal for corporate clients (Brief format), casual for solopreneurs (Deep Dive format)\n\nMorning Motivation System: Generate daily podcasts from your goals and affirmations for personal accountability\nDiscovery Prompt (Internal Drive): \"Find my annual goals, quarterly objectives, and personal development notes.\"\nAnalysis Prompt: \"What specific actions and mindset shifts will move me closer to these goals today?\"\nDissemination: Set hosts as \"coach and future successful self\" using the Debate format to challenge limiting beliefs\nPractice Partner: Create debate-format audios where AI challenges your assumptions\n\n\nPodcast - Deep Dive Format:\nHost Instructions: You are two warm, witty relationship experts creating a retrospective about this couple's year. One host should focus on emotional moments, the other on adventures and growth. Include specific quotes from their messages.\"\nFocus: \"Highlight the journey from January to December, noting seasonal changes in their relationship, challenges overcome, and dreams discussed for the future.\"\nPodcast - Interview Format:\nHost Instructions: \"One host is a romantic historian, the other is the 'voice' of their relationship. Interview style discussing key moments chronologically.\"\nCustom prompt: \"Include their actual words as 'audio quotes' and reflect on why these moments mattered\"\nVideo Overview:\nStyle: \"Create a romantic documentary-style presentation\"\nFocus: \"Structure as 'Seasons of Love' - four segments showing how the relationship evolved each quarter\"\nPrompt: \"Use date/location stamps for each major event discussed.\"\n\n\n\nPitch Practice Partner: Create debate-format audios where Al challenges your\nbusiness assumptions\nDiscovery Prompt (Internal Drive): \"Find my pitch deck, value propositions, and sales scripts\"\nAnalysis Prompt: \"What are the toughest objections a skeptical investor or client might raise? BE BRUTAL.\" BRUTAL.'  - What are the best counterarguments to these?\nDissemination: Use tique format with hosts as \"skeptical investor and defensive founder\" to practice responses\n\n\n\nPersonal Brand Consistency Auditor\nEnsure your message remains powerfend consistent across all platforms.\nWhat to Upload:\nAll your content across platforms\nBrand guidelines and voice docs\nAudience feedback and comments\nCompetitor brand analyses\nSpeaking transcripts\nEmail campaigns\nSocial media posts\n\nDiscovery Prompt: Find personal branding best practices and consistency frameworks from thought leaders.\nAnalysis Prompt: Identify unique phrases, recurring themes, and contradictions to define your brand essence.\nBrand Architecture:  Create platform-specific notebooks to track voice and optimize for different channels.\nAlignment Outputs:\nGenerate brand consistency reports\nCreate voice guideline documents\nProduce brand story podcasts\nDraft message architecture\n\n\nInteractive Portfolio Experienceyr\nTransform static portfolios into dynamic experiences that convert prospects.\nWhat to Upload:\nProject case studies and results\nClient testimonials and feedback\nBefore/after comparisons\nProcess documentation\nAwards and recognition\nMedia coverage and features\nBehind-the-scenes content\nDiscovery Prompt: Find innovative digital portfolio examples and conversion optimization techniques\nAnalysis Prompt: Which elements of these success stories would be most compelling for prospects in similar situations? Create an interactive journey.\nPortfolio Architecture: Create restricted-access notebooks for different prospect types. Track engagement to refine presentation.\n\n\nBest Prompts for Audio Overviews\nhttps://chatgpt.com/c/68e32438-9054-8326-8372-5dbac1649883\n\n\n# 📘 Researcher’s Master Prompt Pack for NotebookLM Audio Overviews\n\n### 🧠 Purpose  \nA unified prompt framework for generating **deep, structured, and technically precise audio overviews** of recent research papers, repos, or blogs — ideal for researchers who want to be *thorough and critical* rather than just informed.\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 Core Prompt — “Single Work Deep Dive”\n\n> **Paste this directly into NotebookLM’s Audio Overview field:**\n\n**Role & Audience**\n- Speak as a **senior researcher** explaining to another researcher.  \n- Be factual, cite **numbers, figures, and page references** when available.  \n- If something is unclear or missing, explicitly say *“not reported”*.  \n\n**Tone & Style**\n- Analytical, neutral, and precise — no hype or vagueness.  \n- Paraphrase equations in plain English and define key variables.  \n- Highlight assumptions, trade-offs, and failure points.\n\n**Deliverable: A 15–20 minute structured overview**  \nOrganize it into these sections:\n\n1. **Problem & Context** – Real-world motivation, prior SOTA, what gap it fills.  \n2. **Contributions** – List verbatim, then interpret practically.  \n3. **Method Walkthrough** –  \n   - High-level flow → each module’s inputs, outputs, and design rationale.  \n   - Note loss functions, priors, and inductive biases.  \n4. **Experimental Setup** –  \n   - Datasets, metrics, baselines, compute budget, ablations, reproducibility.  \n5. **Results & Evidence** –  \n   - Quantitative comparisons (absolute & relative improvements).  \n   - Which ablations actually mattered?  \n6. **Limitations & Threats to Validity** –  \n   - Bias, leakage, cherry-picking, reproducibility caveats.  \n7. **Positioning vs SOTA** –  \n   - Closest prior works, practical deltas, compute vs performance trade-offs.  \n8. **Reproduction Plan** –  \n   - Code/data availability, setup steps, checkpoints, acceptance criteria.  \n9. **Industrialization Readiness** –  \n   - Path to deployment: latency, safety, monitoring, drift control.  \n10. **Actionable Takeaways** –  \n   - 5 concrete steps for an R&D engineer.  \n   - 3 red-flag questions to ask authors before adoption.\n\n**Add a “Skeptic Segment” (2–3 min)**  \nHave an *Explainer* and a *Skeptic* debate weak points, missing evidence, and what data would resolve uncertainty.\n\n**Polish**\n- Begin with a 45-second **executive summary**.  \n- End with a **glossary** of symbols and key terms.  \n- Reference any critical figures or tables.\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 Comparative Overview — “Multiple Works”\n\n> “Create a side-by-side audio briefing comparing {papers}.  \n> Organize into:  \n> 1) shared problem framing  \n> 2) method families  \n> 3) datasets/metrics comparability  \n> 4) who wins where (quantify)  \n> 5) compute/latency trade-offs  \n> 6) robustness/failure modes  \n> 7) practical recommendation tree  \n> 8) missing ablations or open questions.”\n\nAlways ensure every claim is **traceable to a specific source**.\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 Reproducibility Plan\n\n> “Turn this work into a **reproducibility plan** covering:  \n> - Environment (hardware, OS, libraries, CUDA)  \n> - Dataset sources, splits, preprocessing  \n> - Training schedule, hyperparameters, logging  \n> - Key checkpoints and metrics  \n> - Minimal ablations (3 most critical)  \n> - Sanity checks (label shuffle, seed tests)  \n> - Acceptance criteria vs reported metrics  \n> - Common pitfalls (OOM, instability, missing seeds).”\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 From Paper to Production\n\n> “Summarize how to bring this work to **real-world deployment**:  \n> - Inference graph & bottlenecks  \n> - Quantization/pruning/distillation choices  \n> - Confidence gating and rollback plans  \n> - Monitoring for data/performance drift  \n> - License & compliance review  \n> - A/B rollout design and success metrics.  \n> Conclude with a 3-phase roadmap (Week 1, Weeks 2–4, Beyond).”\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 Peer Review (Socratic Critique)\n\n> “Act as a top-tier conference reviewer:  \n> - Best case *for* the paper  \n> - Strongest case *against*  \n> - Missing baselines & external-validity threats  \n> - 3 experiments that would strengthen evidence  \n> - Score for originality, significance, rigor, reproducibility.”\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 Repo-Based Walkthrough\n\n> “If the source includes a GitHub repo:  \n> - Explain the code pipeline and module structure  \n> - Note fragile points (paths, seeds, configs)  \n> - Summarize key config knobs  \n> - Draft a 10-minute smoke test to confirm setup  \n> - Suggest 2–3 GitHub issues to file upstream.”\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 Robotics / Imitation-Learning Add-On\n\nAppend this when working in robotics or embodied AI:\n\n> “Include:  \n> - Observation/action spaces, control frequency, latency  \n> - Sim2Real assumptions and domain randomization  \n> - Safety and failure recovery in contact tasks  \n> - Dataset requirements for imitation learning  \n> - Evaluation under disturbances (lighting, friction, pose)  \n> - Integration sketch with ROS / MoveIt / UR5 + Robotiq setup.”\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 Quick One-Liners (for speed)\n\n- **Deep Dive:**  \n  “Give me a 20-min overview of {paper}: problem → contributions → method → experiments → results (with numbers) → limitations → SOTA → repro plan → industrialization → takeaways.”\n\n- **Compare:**  \n  “Compare {papers} by method, datasets, results, robustness, and deployment trade-offs. End with a decision tree for which to use.”\n\n- **Repro:**  \n  “Generate a reproducibility plan for {paper}: env, data, hparams, ablations, sanity checks, and acceptance metrics.”\n\n---\n\n## 🔹 Config Snippet (Prompt-as-Code)\n\nStore this YAML for reuse:\n\n```yaml\naudio_overview_profile:\n  role: \"senior researcher to senior researcher\"\n  duration_minutes: 18\n  chapters:\n    - Problem & Context\n    - Contributions\n    - Method Walkthrough\n    - Experimental Setup\n    - Results & Ablations\n    - Limitations & Validity\n    - SOTA Positioning\n    - Repro Plan\n    - Industrialization\n    - Actionable Takeaways\n  constraints:\n    - \"Quantify all claims; cite figure/page or say 'not reported'.\"\n    - \"Paraphrase equations; highlight variables and assumptions.\"\n    - \"Add 2–3 min Explainer vs Skeptic debate.\"\n    - \"End with glossary and 5 concrete next steps.\"\n",
