      "id": "gdhzc5uu",
      "title": "ROS2 Refresher",
      "content": "Underlay refers to the core ROS2 installations\nOverlay refers to custom ROS2 installations. In cases of ambiguity, where packages with similar names conflict, the one in the overlay takes precedence.\n\nWorkspace Details\nBuild folder contains all the intermediate files and subfolders for each package present in the source folder \nInstall folder is the final destination where all the executables are stored\n \n\nros2 pkg create --build-type ament_cmake/ament_python name\n\n\nros2 pkg list - List the packages that are recognized within ROS2 env\n\n📦 Types of Dependencies\n1. <depend> - Universal Dependency\n\n```\n<depend>rclpy</depend>\nWhat it means: Needed for all phases (build, export, and execution)\nEquivalent to: Having <build_depend>, <build_export_depend>, and <exec_depend> all together\nUse when: The package is needed everywhere\n2. <exec_depend> - Execution Dependency ⭐ (Your file uses this)\n\n<exec_depend>rclpy</exec_depend><exec_depend>std_msgs</exec_depend>\nWhat it means: Needed only at runtime when executing the node\nBuild time: Not needed during compilation\nUse when: Runtime libraries, Python packages, message packages\n3. <build_depend> - Build-time Dependency\n\n<build_depend>rclcpp</build_depend>\nWhat it means: Needed only during compilation\nRuntime: Not needed when running the node\nUse when: Header files, build tools, compilers\n4. <build_export_depend> - Export Dependency\n\n<build_export_depend>rclcpp</build_depend>\nWhat it means: Needed when other packages build against this package\nUse when: Your package exposes headers/interfaces that others need\n🔍 Your Package Analysis\nYour Python package uses <exec_depend> which is perfect because:\n\n\n<exec_depend>rclpy</exec_depend>        <!-- Python ROS 2 client library --><exec_depend>std_msgs</exec_depend>     <!-- Standard message types --><exec_depend>arduinobot_msgs</exec_depend> <!-- Custom messages -->\nWhy <exec_depend> for Python packages?\nPython is interpreted - no compilation needed\nDependencies loaded at runtime when Python imports modules\nNo build-time compilation of Python files\n\nBest Practises:\nFor Python packages\n<!-- Use exec_depend for Python packages -->\n<exec_depend>rclpy</exec_depend>\n<exec_depend>std_msgs</exec_depend>\n\nFor C++ packages:\n<!-- Headers needed during build -->\n<build_depend>rclcpp</build_depend>\n<build_depend>std_msgs</build_depend>\n\n<!-- Libraries needed at runtime -->\n<exec_depend>rclcpp</exec_depend>\n<exec_depend>std_msgs</exec_depend>\n\n<!-- OR use depend for both -->\n<depend>rclcpp</depend>\n<depend>std_msgs</depend>\n\nFor Message Packages\n<!-- Others need these to build against your messages -->\n<build_export_depend>std_msgs</build_export_depend>\n<exec_depend>std_msgs</exec_depend>\n```\n\n",
