    {
      "id": "8iu20aqa",
      "title": "Foundational Model for Robotics",
      "content": "All robotic systems are fundamentally a combination of the following components: Perception, Actuation & Planning\n\n\nReplacing the Planning Block - First step was to consider LLMs for generating High Level Plans that can be broken down into Low Level Plans - SAY-CAN.GITHUB.IO\nReplacing the Perception Block - Using a VLM - socraticmodels.github.io, innermonologue.github.io, robot-help.github.io\nReplacing the Actuation Block with CODELM - code-as-policies.github.io, robot-teaching.github.io, generative-expressive-motion.github.io\n\n\nVLM + LLM - palm-e.github.io, video-language-planning.github.io\n\nVLM + CODELM - robotics-transformer1.github.io\n\nVLM+LLM_CODELM - robotics-transformer2.github.io, robotics-trasnformer-x.github.io, rt-hierarchy.github.io, sites.google.com/view/rtsara\n\n\nLanguage is great at working at all levels of abstraction.\n\nfrom something like \"move 2mm\" to \"pick up the cup\" to \"be helpful\"\n\nThe idea of grounding robot behaviour in a Constitution built on values that would influence the actions taken by the robot.\n\nConstitutional Embodied AI\n- Semantic Safety\n- Human Preferences\n- Defence in Depth\n- Value Alignment\n\n\n\n\n\n",
