    {
      "id": "pkrfp0in",
      "title": "2025-10-18 — Daily",
      "content": "# Top 3\n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n\n## Tasks\n\n## Journal\n\n## Interview with Aravind Srinivas\n  -   Building AI agents that work for the user to protect their interests and safety over the ad marketers or search engines, or companies\n  -   The idea is that the AI agents would be the middleman and interact with all the ads and campaigns and decide on one that works best for the user. In the process, the user\n      also compensated for switching or buying into, and also the company running the agent gets a cut for the service they are providing\n\n\n## Wins\n",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": "2025-10-18",
      "type": "daily",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2025-10-18T17:48:04.744Z",
