    {
      "id": "9hkcssa7",
      "title": "Important Learning Resources for RL,IL,Sim2Real",
      "content": "Here is a detailed list of all the best video resources and associated details on Robot Learning, Sim2Real, Imitation Learning, and relevant ROS integration/tutorials from this conversation. You can easily copy and use the following in your email:\n\n***\n\n## Robot Learning & Sim2Real Tutorials and Demonstrations\n\n- **Robot Learning: A Tutorial (Oct 2025)**  \n  Comprehensive theory and implementation guide for modern robot learning.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=NXwEN39yrEk\n\n- **Unlocking Scalable Robot Learning in the Real World with Karl Pertsch (ICRA’24 Best Paper)**  \n  Explores state-of-the-art robot learning systems, including industry examples.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vDeuS7V1VqY\n\n- **Foundational Models for Robotics and Scaling DeepRL**  \n  Discusses foundational models and deep reinforcement learning for robotics.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1ZuvCWvj0HM\n\n- **AI Agents Cross from Simulation to Reality as Robots via Sim2Real**  \n  Demonstration of Sim2Real transfer using Gazebo, Isaac Sim, Unity, and ROS.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mWPr16-4_xQ\n\n- **Bridging the Sim-to-Real Gap for Accelerated Robot Training (NVIDIA Cosmos)**  \n  Efficient data generation and Sim2Real iteration for robot learning.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tudMMCq04SA\n\n- **Dr. Akshara Rai: Sim2Real Learning for Home Robots**  \n  Practical transfer from simulation to real home robots, including sensors and ROS usage.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t864-ItmIw0\n\n- **Can ML-Agents Train a Real Robot? A Unity Sim2Real Experiment**  \n  Complete workflow for Sim2Real using Unity ML-Agents Toolkit.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-ZK4p9XFVyQ\n\n- **Lecture 22 Sim2Real and Domain Randomization (UC Berkeley)**  \n  Sim2Real transfer, physics simulation, and practical domain randomization.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ac_W9IgKX2c\n\n- **EAGERx: Graph-Based Framework for Sim2real Robot Learning**  \n  Modelling and transferring learned policies from simulation to real robots.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=D0CQNnTT010\n\n- **Behavioural Cloning using Deep Imitation Learning with Sim2Real transfer**  \n  Step-by-step, self-driving car pipeline with deep imitation learning and Sim2Real deployment using ROS and NVIDIA Jetson Nano.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rejpoogaXOE\n\n***\n\n## Imitation Learning – Implementation and Demos\n\n- **(RA-L 2025) VILP: Imitation Learning with Latent Video Planning**  \n  Video-based imitation learning with implementation details and open-source code.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sfa_AmI0NoI\n\n- **How I Built an Open-Source Synthetic Data Tool to Fix My Imitation Learning Robot**  \n  Hands-on creation of synthetic data for robotic imitation learning tasks.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8K9TBExM6RE\n\n- **Stanford CS25: Robotics and Imitation Learning**  \n  Deep dive lecture into imitation learning and practical robotics.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ct4tdyyNDY4\n\n- **Teaching a Robot to Grasp Real Fish by Imitation Learning**  \n  Real-world robotic grasping using imitation learning from human demonstrations in VR.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ox_uJd6yHzo\n\n***\n\n## Demos and ROS-Integrated Tutorials\n\n- **Simulate RB-KAIROS+ robot with ROS 2: Step-by-Step Tutorial**  \n  Full pipeline for simulation and control of a mobile manipulator robot using ROS2, Gazebo, and RVIZ.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xvE0hjqwJGU\n\n- **ROS2_Control Gazebo Tutorial Robot Simulation (Tesla Bot Example)**  \n  Humanoid robot simulation and control using ROS2 and Gazebo.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PM_1Nb9u-N0\n\n- **ROS and AI Tutorial Playlist**  \n  Playlist covering many AI and robot learning scenarios involving ROS.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLpwJoq86vov9U87KZG_x6w739Mlp07-BG\n\n- **Learn robotics with ROS YouTube Channel**  \n  Multiple implementations, demonstrations and integration videos with ROS.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCHHv_UYPcZGGibNiPhJRpmw/videos\n\n- **Using Isaac Sim with ROS2: Step-by-Step Guide**  \n  Layered examples of using NVIDIA Isaac Sim and ROS2 together.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L1rpxRm0Q1w\n\n***\n\n## Related Articles, Code, & Frameworks\n\n- **MIT EECS: Precision home robots learn with real-to-sim-to-real**  \n  Article on new sim2real/real2sim transfer techniques.  \n  Link: https://www.eecs.mit.edu/precision-home-robots-learn-with-real-to-sim-to-real/\n\n- **A Real-to-Sim-to-Real Approach for Robust Manipulation (RialTo System)**  \n  Robustifying imitation learning policies with digital twin simulation and RL.  \n  Link: https://real-to-sim-to-real.github.io/RialTo/\n\n- **ROBOTIS LAB: Reinforcement learning & imitation learning Sim2Real Tutorials (GitHub)**  \n  Tutorials for RL and imitation learning using ROBOTIS robots, supporting Sim2Real.  \n  Link: https://github.com/ROBOTIS-GIT/robotis_lab\n\n- **Meta: Robots that learn from human videos and simulated interactions**  \n  Frameworks for training robots from internet videos and simulation.  \n  Link: https://ai.meta.com/blog/robots-learning-video-simulation-artificial-visual-cortex-vc-1/\n\n***\n\n## Discussion Threads & Community\n\n- **Reddit: Want to train a humanoid robot to learn from YouTube videos**  \n  Community discussion and project sharing for robot learning from YouTube.  \n  Link: https://www.reddit.com/r/learnmachinelearning/comments/1kv5kyo/want_to_train_a_humanoid_robot_to_learn_from/\n\n- **Reliable Robot Control Lab (YouTube Channel)**  \n  Sim2Real and robust RL research in robotics.  \n  Link: https://www.youtube.com/@r2clab/videos\n\n***\n\nPlease let me know if you want this message sent directly to your email inbox, and specify the preferred email address if I do not already have it.\n\n[1](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ac_W9IgKX2c)\n[2](https://www.eecs.mit.edu/precision-home-robots-learn-with-real-to-sim-to-real/)\n[3](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rejpoogaXOE)\n[4](https://www.linkedin.com/posts/stonet2000_robotics-accessibility-embodiedai-activity-7346751214857932800-2TRr)\n[5](https://techxplore.com/news/2024-07-framework-robots-online-human-videos.html)\n[6](https://ai.meta.com/blog/robots-learning-video-simulation-artificial-visual-cortex-vc-1/)\n[7](https://github.com/ROBOTIS-GIT/robotis_lab)\n[8](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ox_uJd6yHzo)\n[9](https://developer.nvidia.com/blog/training-sim-to-real-transferable-robotic-assembly-skills-over-diverse-geometries/)\n[10](https://real-to-sim-to-real.github.io/RialTo/)",
