      "id": "qk8xz87d",
      "title": "ROS2 Control",
      "content": "The hardware resources are managed by a component called Resource Manager, which interacts with the hardware via two interfaces - Command Interface and State Interface.\n\nThe Control Manager is responsible for bridging the appropriate Controller with the Resource Manager. All the control logics are defined within the Control Manager which are responsible for ensuring the system output \n\n### Integration with Gazebo\n  - Include the ros2 control as a gazebo plugin \n    - Ensure that with conditions, the right versions are loaded - for versions after Humble, the plugin is loaded from gz_ros2_control, and for Humble, it's loaded from ign_ro2_control\n    - The same applies while loading the hardware interface as well - there exist separate hardware interfaces for real and simulated robots.",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": "y9081w3r",
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "note",
