    {
      "id": "xv8cbtg9",
      "title": "Think Faster, Talk Smarter",
      "content": "Important Takeaways:\n- Tame the anxiety\n  - If not for any other reason, but at least so that our audience doesn't feel the tension(second-hand anxiety), we should learn to manage our anxiety\n    - Manage both symptoms and sources \n      - Ways to manage symptoms are:\n        - Take a deep belly breath\n        - Hold something cold\n        - Drink hot water or chew gum\n      - Ways to manage the sources are:\n        - Feel nervous thinking about the goal\n          - Become present-oriented - engage in conversations, tongue twisters\n- Maximize mediocrity\n  - Reduce cognitive load\n- Mind your mindset\n  - See things as an opportunity  \n    - FOUR MINDSET TOOLS - Not yet; Yes, and; Next play; Missed takes\n- Don't just do something\n  -\n\n        ",
      "tags": [
        "selfimprovement",
        "communication"
      ],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "note",
