      "id": "28kuutq9",
      "title": "2026-03-02 — Daily",
      "content": "# Top 3\n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n\n## Tasks\n\n## Journal\n\n## Wins\n\n# Thinkschool - Geopolitics\n- Is Iran Innocent?\n  - Western media played a key role painting the image of Iran as a nation of terror\n  - The nuclear power of Iran was gifted by the US and US heavily relied on Iran for Oil\n  - In 1950s soon after the end of World War 2, it was believed that:\n    - More Oil = More Power\n    - Country with nuclear power rules\n  - Iran porvided a base for sourcing oil and also territory for setting up american bases allowing them to work as powerful entity next to the USSR\n  - Until 1970s till the upcoming of political parties Iran functioned with American culture and lifestyle deeply embedded in them. All the money they earned by selling oil either went to the\n    western companies or went to the elite and rich of the country with less or none going to the actual poor.\n  - 100 million dollars were on the party by Iran Shah \n  - Khomeni came as a saviour revolting against the careless rule of the existing Shah. Reforms by him that turned America into their enemy:\n    - Islamic nation\n    - Removed democracy and implemented autocracy\n    - Took about 50 americans as hostage\n    - Cancelled all operations of American oil companies\n  - As a response to this Americans froze almost all Iranian assets in the US\n  - Openly supported the war between Iraq and Iran taking the side of Sadham Hussain\n  - Barrack Obama released all sanctions on Iran in return for a no nuclear power promise\n  - In this world of ruthless geopolitics no there is no permenant friend or enemies and only permenant intrests",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": "2026-03-02",
      "type": "daily",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2026-03-02T18:26:57.945Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-02T22:07:27.645Z",
      "attachments": [],
      "links": [],
      "journal": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "lqb36zam",
      "title": "2026-03-03 — Daily",
      "content": "# Top 3\n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n\n## Tasks\n\n## Journal\n\n## Wins\n",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": "2026-03-03",
      "type": "daily",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2026-03-03T18:09:51.406Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-04T07:54:19.240Z",
      "attachments": [],
      "links": [],
      "deletedAt": null,
      "journal": "I wasn't entirely happy today but the irony is today is one such day where a lot of things went well.  I walked to and fro to office. Sent my phd first  application finally. I was late to sent it however I did put together a good content overall.\n\n\nKunju is still at her home. I miss her but it's so cute how she finds time to talk to me whilst at home. Today she went to sleep early but the fun thing is in between she woke up and gave me a call. I just instantly fell in love. I think these are some of the best things about her! I really miss her and wished she was with me in person.\n\nToday we went through all that we managed ",
      "mood": "🙂"
    },
    {
      "id": "b7r88wuh",
      "title": "2026-03-04 — Daily",
      "content": "# Top 3\n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n\n## Tasks\n\n## Journal\n\n## Wins\n",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": "2026-03-04",
      "type": "daily",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2026-03-04T07:44:35.193Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-03-05T07:15:23.728Z",
      "attachments": [],
      "links": [],
      "deletedAt": null,
      "journal": "Today wasn't so much fun. For some reason I was super low on energy. Couldn't complete a lot of work at office as well. Came back home early. Ordered from outside. Ate heartful. Didn't really do much but compensate for the sleep.\n\nWoke up in the evening talking to Kunju. It was fun. We did brought in some topics which were fun lol😬. Went for a quick run and skipped for a while. \n\nForgot to call Obaid chacha. He got me shocked with his marriage call off news. Got to talk to him about it in detail.\n\n\nAnjumma had a new set of issues 😅. She had to get some dresses for her women's day event.  Took a class for her on the importance of protein and creatine🙂.\n\n\nTalked to Kunju before going to sleep. Typical Kunju...was zoned out for most part of the conversation. But I know her...I love her. ",
      "mood": "😐"
