      "id": "dbfu8rxm",
      "title": "Daily Research Read - Self Supervised Learning, JEPA, World Models and the Future of AI - Part 2",
      "content": "Inference through Optimization is not a new concept but something that has been extensively used in the classical methods\n- Optimization based inference enables zero-shot learning\n  - It can find innovative solutions to unseen problems\n- Optimization based inference is also the fundamental in System 2\n  - System 1 refers to actions that are taken with marginal to no thought whereas System 2 refers to the decisions that are taken by thinking about it by using a mental model of the world\n    to predict the outcome of the particular actions that could be taken.\n\nHowever the hero of the current modern world - LLMs work on the principle of Autoregression\n  - Outputs one token after another through FFN predictions\n    - Tokens could be anything from words to image patches to speech segments - hence only works for discreete domains\nLimitations of AR based models\n  - Tend to basically produce outputs based on a fixed number computations for producing any single token hence the only way to entice a system of this type to spend more computational resources on a question is by tricking it into producing more tokens - popularily used technique for this is chain of thoughts.\n\nThe design of LLM is fundamentally faulty because the idea that it works on solely based on picking the most accurate or probable next token, there is always a chance it could pick a token that falls outside the subtree of correct answers,\nP(correct) = (1-e)^n\nwhere n - length of the answer\nP(correct) - probability that answer of length n is correct assuming independence of errors\ne - probability of accepting a token outside the subtree of correct answers\n\n\nThe whole possible tokens for a sequence could be represented as a tree where the list of correct answers could be represented as a subtree \n  - Because its a tree as you start diverging more and more from the correct answers the harder it becomes to get back on track\n ",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": "tikubsii",
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "note",
