      "id": "sextncsp",
      "title": "Openclaw - Nemoclaw",
      "content": "Openclaw works like a plumming tool that primarily connects the text/messaging apps with the localhost and the popular llms and tools/skills \n\n- Openclaw as an idea blew up because it was able to do something alot of AI companies offered but did not succeed. On top of it, openclaw was able to run locally with all the data being stored in the local system.\n\n- The key risk is that agentic system could access information, execute code and commuicate externally.\n\n- Some potential threats in suAnmch architecture are as follows:\n  - Any website opened in the past could silently open a connection back to you system via Websocket and acces system data\n  - Prompt Injection - Embed malicious instructions in the scrapped websites that cld invoke unprecedented actions\n \nNvidia Playbook for Dominance:\n  - Built CUDA and pulled developer community into GPU programming with NVIDIA HW\n  - For AI training they built platform layer under all popular AI libraries like Pytorch and TF again pulling developers into consuming more of their HW\n  - Same strategy with agents now\n    - Nemoclaw makes it safe for enterprises to use Agentic Workflows\n      Enterprises need agents - agents need compute - aompute runs on Nvidia\n\n - Nemoclaw doesnt fundamentally use any revolutionarly tech besides and tried and tested sec stack of Linux\n - It basically packages all the standard security stack at the os level to regulate the functions of the agent\n - There is a policy engine that enforces rules at the OS level ",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "note",
      "pinned": false,
