      "id": "7t0fvh5v",
      "title": "SIm2Sim & ADC - Debugging Journal",
      "content": "# Sim2Sim Debugging Journal — UR5e Pick-and-Place in Isaac Sim\n\n**Created:** 2026-04-11\n**Machine:** HP Z6 G5 A, 2× RTX 6000 Ada (49 GB each), 125 GB RAM, Ubuntu 22.04\n**Isaac Sim:** 5.0, conda env `tvp_nv_stack` (Python 3.11)\n**Policy Env:** conda env `tvp_ilab_py310` — lerobot 0.4.1, torch 2.7.1+cu126, Python 3.10\n**Model:** `act_ur5e_pnp_145ep_200k_kl01_dec1` — ACT architecture, chunk_size=100\n**Dataset:** `ur5e_pnp_full_v2` — 145 episodes, 58,343 frames, 20 Hz\n**USD Scene:** `ur5e_robotiq_gripper_adc_cell_with_camera_lerobot_inference_v1.usd`\n\n---\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n1. [System Overview](#1-system-overview)\n2. [The Problem](#2-the-problem)\n3. [Diagnostic Methodology — Strip Band-Aids First](#3-diagnostic-methodology)\n4. [Offline Policy Diagnosis — Policy is GOOD](#4-offline-policy-diagnosis)\n5. [USD Scene Bugs Found & Fixed](#5-usd-scene-bugs-found--fixed)\n   - [Bug 1: Normalizer Explosion (std=0)](#bug-1-normalizer-explosion-std0)\n   - [Bug 2: `purpose=\"guide\"` Makes PhysX Ignore Prims](#bug-2-purposeguide-makes-physx-ignore-prims)\n   - [Bug 3: Cube Missing CollisionAPI](#bug-3-cube-missing-collisionapi)\n   - [Bug 4: No Joint Drive Stiffness/Damping](#bug-4-no-joint-drive-stiffnessdamping)\n   - [Bug 5: USD Instancing Prevents Finger Edits](#bug-5-usd-instancing-prevents-finger-edits)\n   - [Bug 6: Q_ Board Zones Too Thin for PhysX](#bug-6-q_-board-zones-too-thin-for-physx)\n6. [Band-Aid Fixes Attempted & Reverted](#6-band-aid-fixes-attempted--reverted)\n7. [Training Data Analysis](#7-training-data-analysis)\n8. [Scripts Created](#8-scripts-created)\n9. [Key Learnings & Interview Insights](#9-key-learnings--interview-insights)\n\n---\n\n## 1. System Overview\n\n```\nTraining Data (real UR5e robot)\n  │\n  ▼\nLeRobot Dataset (145 episodes, 20 Hz, 4 cameras × 512×512)\n  │\n  ▼\nACT Policy Training (200k steps, chunk_size=100)\n  │\n  ▼\nTrained Model Checkpoint\n  │\n  ▼\nPolicy Bridge Node (ROS 2 Humble)  ←→  Isaac Sim 5.0 (simulated UR5e)\n  │                                        │\n  ├── Reads: 4 camera images + 14-dim state (7 pos + 7 vel)\n  └── Publishes: 7-dim action (6 arm joints + 1 gripper)\n```\n\n**Model architecture:**\n- ACT (Action Chunking with Transformers)\n- dim_model=512, n_heads=8, n_decoder_layers=1\n- kl_weight=0.1, chunk_size=100\n- resnet18 backbone for 4 cameras\n- 14-dim state input (7 joint positions + 7 joint velocities)\n- 7-dim action output (6 arm joint positions + 1 gripper position)\n\n**Observation state layout (14-dim):**\n```\n[0]  position.shoulder_pan_joint\n[1]  position.shoulder_lift_joint\n[2]  position.elbow_joint\n[3]  position.wrist_1_joint\n[4]  position.wrist_2_joint\n[5]  position.wrist_3_joint\n[6]  position.robotiq_85_left_knuckle_joint (gripper)\n[7]  velocity.shoulder_pan_joint\n[8]  velocity.shoulder_lift_joint\n[9]  velocity.elbow_joint\n[10] velocity.wrist_1_joint\n[11] velocity.wrist_2_joint\n[12] velocity.wrist_3_joint\n[13] velocity.robotiq_85_left_knuckle_joint (gripper velocity)  ← THE PROBLEM INDEX\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. The Problem\n\nAfter deploying the trained ACT policy into Isaac Sim, the robot demonstrated\nthat it learned the **task structure** (reach → close gripper → transport →\nopen → return home) but exhibited several failure modes:\n\n- Arm goes to correct general area but misses the cube center\n- Gripper closes but cube falls through / passes through fingers\n- Cube falls through the board surface\n- Robot arm flops under gravity (can't hold poses)\n- Jerky/discontinuous motion at chunk boundaries\n\n**Initial instinct was to fix symptoms** — add gripper latches, velocity\nclamping, etc. This was the wrong approach.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Diagnostic Methodology\n\n### Philosophy: \"Strip all band-aids, diagnose properly\"\n\nAfter multiple band-aid attempts failed, we adopted a rigorous approach:\n\n1. **Revert ALL code-level band-aids** — gripper latch, velocity clamping,\n   everything. Return `policy_bridge_node.py` and `action_to_jointstate_adapter.py`\n   to clean passthrough.\n\n2. **Ask one question first:** \"Is the policy correct offline?\"\n   - If YES → problem is in deployment/physics/timing\n   - If NO → problem is in training/data/normalizer\n\n3. **Only after diagnosis** make targeted fixes with clear rationale.\n\nThis approach saved days of chasing symptoms and led directly to the real bugs.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Offline Policy Diagnosis\n\n**Script:** `rosetta/scripts/diagnose_policy.py`\n\n**What it does:** Loads the trained model checkpoint, feeds it real\nobservations from training episodes, compares predicted actions against\nground-truth recorded actions.\n\n**Key API used:**\n```python\nfrom lerobot.policies.factory import make_pre_post_processors\npreprocessor, postprocessor = make_pre_post_processors(\n    policy_cfg=policy.config,\n    pretrained_path=policy_path,\n    dataset_stats=dataset_stats\n)\n```\n\n**Results:**\n```\nVERDICT: POLICY IS ACCURATE OFFLINE\n  Arm joints MAE:    0.01 rad  (~0.6 degrees)\n  Gripper MAE:       0.004 rad\n  Action chunks:     Smooth, continuous\n  Gripper signal:    Clean, binary (open/close)\n```\n\n**Conclusion:** The policy learned the task correctly. The problem is in\ndeployment — specifically in the **Isaac Sim scene physics setup**.\n\n---\n\n## 5. USD Scene Bugs Found & Fixed\n\n### Bug 1: Normalizer Explosion (std=0)\n\n| | |\n|---|---|\n| **Category** | Model preprocessing |\n| **Severity** | Critical — model completely broken without fix |\n| **File** | `pretrained_model/policy_preprocessor_step_3_normalizer_processor.safetensors` |\n| **Symptom** | All model outputs were garbage |\n| **Root cause** | `observation.state.std[13]` (gripper velocity) was `0.0` in training stats |\n| **Why it happened** | During teleop recording, the gripper velocity was always exactly 0 in the dataset (discrete position commands, no continuous velocity). MEAN_STD normalizer computes `(x - mean) / (std + 1e-8)`. With std≈0, any tiny nonzero velocity in simulation gets amplified to ~10⁸ |\n| **Fix** | Patched `observation.state.std[13]` from `0.0` → `1.0` in the safetensors file |\n| **Verification** | After fix, model outputs became reasonable |\n| **Status** | ✅ KEPT — legitimate data/normalizer bug |\n\n**Learning:** Always inspect normalizer statistics before deployment. Zero-std\nfeatures are a classic trap — they mean the feature had zero variance in\ntraining, so the normalizer division explodes on any out-of-distribution value.\n\n---\n\n### Bug 2: `purpose=\"guide\"` Makes PhysX Ignore Prims\n\n| | |\n|---|---|\n| **Category** | USD/PhysX physics setup |\n| **Severity** | Critical — all collision geometry was invisible to physics |\n| **Prims affected** | Finger pad colliders, board collision plane |\n| **Symptom** | Cube fell through board, gripper passed through cube |\n| **Root cause** | When creating invisible collision geometry, the code used `CreatePurposeAttr(\"guide\")`. In USD, `purpose=\"guide\"` means \"this prim is for visualization guides only\" — **PhysX honors this and skips the prim entirely** for collision detection |\n| **Fix** | Changed to `visibility=\"invisible\"` + `purpose=\"default\"` instead. Added repair passes to fix existing prims |\n| **Status** | ✅ FIXED in `isaacsim_scene_setup.py` |\n\n**The wrong way (what we did initially):**\n```python\n# BAD: PhysX will completely ignore this prim!\nUsdGeom.Imageable(prim).CreatePurposeAttr(\"guide\")\n```\n\n**The correct way:**\n```python\n# GOOD: Hidden from rendering, but PhysX still sees it\nUsdGeom.Imageable(prim).GetVisibilityAttr().Set(\"invisible\")\n# purpose stays \"default\" (or don't set it at all)\n```\n\n**Learning:** In USD/PhysX, there are two independent visibility systems:\n- **`visibility`** = rendering only (invisible/inherited). PhysX ignores this.\n- **`purpose`** = semantic classification (default/guide/proxy/render). PhysX\n  DOES check this — `purpose=\"guide\"` means \"not a real object, skip for\n  simulation.\"\n\nThis is a subtle but devastating distinction. One wrong attribute choice and\nyour entire collision setup is silently disabled.\n\n---\n\n### Bug 3: Cube Missing CollisionAPI\n\n| | |\n|---|---|\n| **Category** | USD/PhysX physics setup |\n| **Severity** | Critical — cube was non-collidable |\n| **Prim** | `/Test_Cube` |\n| **Symptom** | Cube fell through everything, gripper passed through cube |\n| **Root cause** | The cube prim had `RigidBodyAPI` and `MassAPI` applied, but **NOT `CollisionAPI`**. Without CollisionAPI, PhysX treats the prim as a phantom — it has mass and responds to gravity, but nothing can collide with it |\n| **Fix** | `UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI.Apply(cube_prim)` |\n| **Status** | ✅ FIXED in `isaacsim_scene_setup.py` |\n\n**Learning:** In USD Physics, the three APIs serve different purposes:\n- `RigidBodyAPI` = \"this object moves under physics\" (gravity, forces)\n- `MassAPI` = \"this object has mass\" (for inertia computation)\n- `CollisionAPI` = \"this object participates in collision detection\"\n\n**You need all three** for a fully interactive physics object. Having\nRigidBody+Mass but no Collision means the object falls under gravity but\npasses through everything like a ghost.\n\n---\n\n### Bug 4: No Joint Drive Stiffness/Damping\n\n| | |\n|---|---|\n| **Category** | USD/PhysX articulation |\n| **Severity** | High — robot couldn't hold any pose |\n| **Joints affected** | All 6 UR5e arm joints + 6 Robotiq gripper joints |\n| **Symptom** | Robot arm flopped/sagged under gravity, couldn't hold positions |\n| **Root cause** | The articulation joint prims had no `drive:angular:physics:stiffness` or `drive:angular:physics:damping` attributes. Without these, the joints have zero resistance — they're like un-powered hinges |\n| **Fix** | Set stiffness/damping on all joints: |\n\n```\nArm joints (6):     stiffness=10000 N·m/rad,  damping=1000 N·m·s/rad\nGripper joints (6): stiffness=1000 N·m/rad,   damping=100 N·m·s/rad\nDrive type:         \"force\" (torque-based, standard for position-controlled articulations)\n```\n\n| **Status** | ✅ FIXED in `isaacsim_scene_setup.py` |\n\n**Learning:** In PhysX articulations, joint drives are what make a robot\n\"motorized.\" Without stiffness, setting a joint target has no effect — the\njoint won't resist external forces (gravity, contact). The drive acts as a\nPD controller: `torque = stiffness * (target - current) - damping * velocity`.\nToo low and the robot flops. Too high and it vibrates. 10000/1000 is a good\nstarting point for a 10kg-payload arm like UR5e.\n\n---\n\n### Bug 5: USD Instancing Prevents Finger Edits\n\n| | |\n|---|---|\n| **Category** | USD scene structure |\n| **Severity** | Medium — blocked all finger collider creation |\n| **Prim** | `/World/ur` (robot root) |\n| **Symptom** | Cannot create child prims under finger links |\n| **Root cause** | Robot was imported with `instanceable=True`. USD instancing makes prims share a prototype — descendant prims become **instance proxies** that are read-only. You cannot add new children (like colliders) to instance proxies |\n| **Fix** | `robot_prim.SetInstanceable(False)` + walk all descendants |\n| **Status** | ✅ FIXED in `isaacsim_scene_setup.py` |\n\n**Learning:** USD instancing is a performance optimization (share geometry\nacross multiple instances of the same asset). But it makes the prim hierarchy\nread-only. If you need to modify a robot's sub-meshes (add colliders, change\nmaterials), you must disable instancing first. This is a common trap when\nimporting URDF/MJCF robots into Isaac Sim.\n\n---\n\n### Bug 6: Q_ Board Zones Too Thin for PhysX\n\n| | |\n|---|---|\n| **Category** | USD/PhysX collision geometry |\n| **Severity** | High — cube fell through the board |\n| **Prims** | `Q_TL`, `Q_TR`, `Q_BL`, `Q_BR` (visual quadrant zones) |\n| **Symptom** | Cube fell through the board even with CollisionAPI on the Q_ zones |\n| **Root cause** | The Q_ zones are visual cubes with `scale=(0.4, 0.2, 0.005)` — only 5mm thick in Z. PhysX's discrete collision detection can miss very thin objects, especially with fast-moving objects (tunneling). Additionally, MeshCollision with `boundingCube` approximation on such thin geometry can produce unreliable results |\n| **Fix** | Created a dedicated collision plane: an invisible cube at `board_collision_plane` with size `(0.9, 0.5, 0.01)` centered at the board surface Z=0.005. Also added CollisionAPI to Q_ zones as belt-and-suspenders |\n| **Status** | ✅ FIXED in `isaacsim_scene_setup.py` |\n\n**Learning:** For collision surfaces, don't rely on visual geometry that\nhappens to be very thin. Create dedicated collision primitives with reasonable\nthickness (≥1cm). PhysX's `convexDecomposition` or `boundingCube` approximations\nare meant for complex visual meshes — for simple flat surfaces, a properly-sized\ncollision box is much more reliable.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Band-Aid Fixes Attempted & Reverted\n\nThese were all applied at the code level before proper diagnosis. **All reverted.**\n\n| Fix | Where | What | Why Reverted |\n|-----|-------|------|-------------|\n| Gripper Latch | `action_to_jointstate_adapter.py` | Lock gripper at max when closing detected | Masked policy's actual gripper signal; if policy is correct, latch is unnecessary |\n| Per-Joint Velocity Clamping (Adapter) | `action_to_jointstate_adapter.py` | Limit joint delta to 0.05 rad/step | Clamped against wrong reference (adapter's last value, not robot's actual position) |\n| Per-Joint Velocity Clamping (Executor) | `policy_bridge_node.py` | Same clamping but in executor loop | Hid whether the policy or the timing was producing jumps |\n\n**Key insight:** Band-aids mask symptoms and prevent diagnosis. The correct\napproach is: diagnose offline first, then fix the actual root cause.\n\nFull details: `rosetta/BAND_AID_FIXES_LOG.md`\n\n---\n\n## 7. Training Data Analysis\n\n### Home Position (Start of Every Episode)\nExtremely consistent across all 145 episodes (std < 0.001 rad):\n\n| Joint | Value (rad) | Value (deg) |\n|-------|-------------|-------------|\n| shoulder_pan | 1.5400 | 88.23° |\n| shoulder_lift | -1.6199 | -92.81° |\n| elbow | 1.4000 | 80.22° |\n| wrist_1 | -1.2000 | -68.76° |\n| wrist_2 | -1.6001 | -91.68° |\n| wrist_3 | -0.1100 | -6.30° |\n| gripper | 0.0006 | ~0° (open) |\n\nAll velocities ≈ 0 at start (robot stationary).\n\n### Cube Placement Distribution\n- **Source quadrant:** ALL 145 episodes start with cube in **Q_TL** (Top-Left)\n- **Cube position was NOT recorded** in the dataset (no XY observation)\n- The policy uses **vision only** (4 cameras) to locate the cube\n\n**Cube placement varied significantly within Q_TL** (computed via UR5e forward\nkinematics at the moment of grasp):\n\n| Axis | Mean | Std | Span | Physical |\n|------|------|-----|------|----------|\n| X (lateral) | 0.2125 m | 0.0946 m | 0.3618 m | **36 cm** |\n| Y (depth) | -0.4975 m | 0.0367 m | 0.1708 m | **17 cm** |\n| Z (height) | 0.1958 m | 0.0025 m | 0.0105 m | ~1 cm (board surface) |\n\nAll coordinates in UR5e base frame (DH forward kinematics).\n\n### Task Distribution\n| Task | Count | Percentage |\n|------|-------|------------|\n| Q_TL → blue_TR | 55 | 38% |\n| Q_TL → red_BR | 56 | 39% |\n| Q_TL → yellow_BL | 34 | 23% |\n\n### Recommended Sim Test Positions (UR5e base frame)\n| Label | X (m) | Y (m) | Notes |\n|-------|-------|-------|-------|\n| Center (mean) | 0.2125 | -0.4975 | Highest success probability |\n| P25 | 0.1379 | -0.5196 | Easy |\n| P75 | 0.2909 | -0.4716 | Easy |\n| Min (edge) | 0.0120 | -0.5929 | Edge case |\n| Max (edge) | 0.3737 | -0.4221 | Edge case |\n\n> **Note:** These are in the UR5e base frame. Offset by the robot's world\n> position in Isaac Sim to get USD world-frame coordinates.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Scripts Created\n\nAll scripts are in `rosetta/scripts/`. The Isaac Sim scripts run in the\n**Script Editor** (Window → Script Editor) inside Isaac Sim.\n\n### `isaacsim_scene_setup.py` (964 lines) — The Main Setup Script\n**Purpose:** One-shot idempotent scene setup for sim2sim deployment.\n**Run in:** Isaac Sim Script Editor\n**Idempotent:** Yes — safe to run multiple times, skips already-done steps.\n\n**What it does (7 steps):**\n1. **INSPECT** — Prints scene structure (cube, robot, board, colliders, materials, lights, cameras)\n2. **CUBE PHYSICS** — Applies RigidBodyAPI + CollisionAPI + MassAPI, sets mass=0.03 kg\n3. **DISABLE INSTANCING** — Sets `instanceable=False` on robot and all descendants\n4. **FRICTION MATERIAL** — Creates `/GripFrictionMaterial` with static=2.0, dynamic=2.0\n5. **FINGER COLLIDERS** — Adds invisible box colliders to 4 finger links with `visibility=\"invisible\"` (NOT `purpose=\"guide\"`!), applies CollisionAPI, binds friction\n6. **QUADRANT BOARD** — Creates invisible collision plane under board, adds CollisionAPI to Q_ zones, binds friction\n6b. **JOINT DRIVES** — Sets stiffness/damping on all arm (10000/1000) and gripper (1000/100) joints, drive type=\"force\"\n6c. **LIGHTING** — Enforces DomeLight + DistantLight to match training environment\n7. **VERIFY** — Checks everything with ✓/✗ marks, prints summary\n\n**Key config section (top of file):**\n```python\nCUBE_PATH = \"/Test_Cube\"\nROBOT_PATH = \"/World/ur\"\nCUBE_MASS_KG = 0.03\nARM_DRIVE_STIFFNESS = 10000.0\nARM_DRIVE_DAMPING = 1000.0\nGRIPPER_DRIVE_STIFFNESS = 1000.0\nGRIPPER_DRIVE_DAMPING = 100.0\nFRICTION_STATIC = 2.0\nFRICTION_DYNAMIC = 2.0\nBOARD_COLLIDER_SIZE = (0.9, 0.5, 0.01)\n```\n\n**Includes repair passes** for the `purpose=\"guide\"` bug — if any prim from a\nprevious broken run has `purpose=\"guide\"`, it's automatically repaired to\n`purpose=\"default\"` + `visibility=\"invisible\"`.\n\n**Saves report to:** `/tmp/isaacsim_scene_setup_report.txt`\n\n---\n\n### `isaacsim_scene_inspect.py` (382 lines) — Read-Only Inspector\n**Purpose:** Comprehensive read-only scene dump for understanding what's there.\n**Run in:** Isaac Sim Script Editor\n**Modifies scene:** No (read-only)\n\n**Prints 10+ sections:**\n- Stage info (up-axis, meters-per-unit)\n- Top-level prims and types\n- Full scene tree\n- Physics scene settings (gravity, solver iterations, timestep)\n- Cube: position, size, mass, physics APIs, materials\n- Robot joints: names, types, limits, current values\n- Robot links: all with physics APIs\n- Cameras: position, orientation, focal length, aperture, clipping\n- Lights: type, position, intensity, color temperature (with authored/default tags)\n- Keyword search (any prim containing \"board\", \"quadrant\", \"zone\", \"target\")\n- All rigid bodies in scene\n- Material bindings\n\n**Output saved to:** `/tmp/isaacsim_scene_inspect.txt`\n\n---\n\n### `isaacsim_debug_colliders.py` (145 lines) — Collider Diagnostic\n**Purpose:** Focused dump of physics properties on collision-relevant prims.\n**Run in:** Isaac Sim Script Editor\n**Modifies scene:** No (read-only)\n\n**Dumps for each prim:**\n- Applied schemas (RigidBodyAPI, CollisionAPI, MassAPI, MeshCollisionAPI)\n- `visibility` and `purpose` attributes (the critical distinction!)\n- Cube size/extent/scale\n- Xform (translate, scale)\n- Material bindings\n- Articulation root info\n\n**Covers:** All 4 finger pad colliders, `/Test_Cube`, board collision plane,\nground plane, articulation root.\n\n---\n\n### `diagnose_policy.py` (539 lines) — Offline Policy Evaluation\n**Purpose:** Answer \"Is the policy correct?\" without running Isaac Sim.\n**Run in:** Terminal with `tvp_ilab_py310` conda env\n**Modifies scene:** No\n\n**Usage:**\n```bash\nconda activate tvp_ilab_py310\npython diagnose_policy.py \\\n    --policy_path /data/tvp_ws/rlearning_ws/outputs/act_ur5e_pnp_145ep_200k_kl01_dec1/checkpoints/200000/pretrained_model \\\n    --dataset_root /data/tvp_ws/rlearning_ws/data/lerobot_dataset/ur5e_pnp_full_v2 \\\n    --episodes 0 1 2 50 100 140 \\\n    --output_dir /data/tvp_ws/rlearning_ws/diagnostic_output\n```\n\n**Outputs:**\n1. Per-joint trajectory plots (predicted vs ground-truth) for each episode\n2. Per-joint error statistics (MAE, max error) across all episodes\n3. Gripper signal analysis (clean or noisy?)\n4. Action chunk smoothness analysis (inter-step delta histogram)\n5. Summary text report\n\n**Verdict from running:** Policy is accurate offline. Arm MAE = 0.01 rad,\nGripper MAE = 0.004 rad.\n\n---\n\n## 9. Key Learnings & Interview Insights\n\n### 1. \"Diagnose before you fix\"\nThe biggest time-waster was applying band-aid fixes before understanding the\nroot cause. Multiple days were spent on gripper latches and velocity clamping\nthat were all reverted. One diagnostic script (`diagnose_policy.py`) proved in\nminutes that the policy was correct — shifting focus to the real problem (physics\nsetup).\n\n### 2. USD `purpose` vs `visibility` — a devastating subtlety\nThis is perhaps the most non-obvious bug. USD has two visibility concepts:\n- `visibility` = rendering only → PhysX ignores this\n- `purpose=\"guide\"` = semantic \"not real\" → PhysX honors this and skips collision\n\nUsing `purpose=\"guide\"` to hide collision geometry from the camera is correct\nsemantically but catastrophic physically. Use `visibility=\"invisible\"` instead.\n\n### 3. The three APIs you need for a physics object in USD\n```\nRigidBodyAPI  →  \"I move under physics\"\nMassAPI       →  \"I have mass and inertia\"\nCollisionAPI  →  \"I participate in collision detection\"\n```\nMissing any one of these creates a subtle failure:\n- No RigidBody: object is static (which may be intentional)\n- No Mass: auto-computed from geometry (usually fine)\n- No Collision: **ghost object** — has mass, falls under gravity, but passes through everything\n\n### 4. Joint drives = motors for your robot\nWithout `drive:angular:physics:stiffness` and `drive:angular:physics:damping`,\nsetting a joint target position does nothing. The joint has no PD controller to\ntrack the target. The robot is just a set of freely-swinging linkages.\n\n### 5. USD instancing = read-only children\nInstanced prims share a prototype. You cannot add new child prims to an\ninstance. Must `SetInstanceable(False)` before modifying the robot's internals.\n\n### 6. Thin collision geometry is unreliable\nA 5mm-thick visual cube used for collision will experience tunneling at any\nreasonable simulation timestep. Use dedicated collision primitives with\n≥1cm thickness.\n\n### 7. Zero-std features in normalizers\nIf a feature has zero variance in training data (e.g., gripper velocity is\nalways 0 during recording), the MEAN_STD normalizer will divide by ≈0, producing\nvalues of ~10⁸ at inference. Either:\n- Remove the feature from the state vector\n- Set std to 1.0 (passthrough normalization)\n- Use a more robust normalization scheme\n\n### 8. Vision-based policies don't store object poses\nThe cube position isn't in the dataset state vector — the policy relies entirely\non camera images to locate the cube. This means success depends on:\n- Camera placement matching between training and deployment\n- Lighting matching between training and deployment\n- Visual appearance of the cube and board being similar\n\n### 9. Idempotent scripts for reproducibility\nThe setup script is designed to be run multiple times safely. Every step checks\nif its work is already done before making changes. This is critical for:\n- Sharing with teammates\n- Recovering from scene corruption\n- Running on different USD files\n\n### 10. Forward kinematics to infer unrecorded quantities\nEven though cube XY position wasn't recorded, we could infer the placement\ndistribution by computing UR5e forward kinematics at the grasp frame. The\nend-effector position at the moment of grasp ≈ the cube position. This gave us\na 36×17 cm placement envelope within Q_TL — useful for designing sim test positions.\n\n---\n\n## Appendix A: Complete USD Change Table\n\nEvery modification the setup script makes to the USD scene:\n\n| Prim | Change | Why |\n|------|--------|-----|\n| `/Test_Cube` | Apply `RigidBodyAPI` | Make cube a dynamic physics object |\n| `/Test_Cube` | Apply `CollisionAPI` | **Critical**: without this, cube is a ghost |\n| `/Test_Cube` | Apply `MassAPI`, mass=0.03 kg | Lightweight cube the gripper can hold |\n| `/Test_Cube` | Bind `/GripFrictionMaterial` (physics purpose) | High friction between cube and fingers |\n| `/World/ur` | `SetInstanceable(False)` + all descendants | Allow creating new child prims (colliders) |\n| `/World/ur/.../robotiq_85_left_finger_tip_link/collisions/pad_collider` | Create Cube, CollisionAPI, visibility=invisible | Box collider for left finger tip |\n| `/World/ur/.../robotiq_85_right_finger_tip_link/collisions/pad_collider` | Create Cube, CollisionAPI, visibility=invisible | Box collider for right finger tip |\n| `/World/ur/.../robotiq_85_left_inner_knuckle_link/collisions/pad_collider` | Create Cube, CollisionAPI, visibility=invisible | Box collider for left inner knuckle |\n| `/World/ur/.../robotiq_85_right_inner_knuckle_link/collisions/pad_collider` | Create Cube, CollisionAPI, visibility=invisible | Box collider for right inner knuckle |\n| All 4 pad_collider prims | Bind `/GripFrictionMaterial` (physics purpose) | High friction on finger surfaces |\n| All 4 pad_collider prims | `purpose=\"default\"` (repair if `\"guide\"`) | **Critical**: `purpose=\"guide\"` makes PhysX skip the prim |\n| `/GripFrictionMaterial` | Create UsdShade.Material + PhysicsMaterialAPI | sf=2.0, df=2.0, restitution=0.0 |\n| `/World/QuadrantBoard/board_collision_plane` | Create Cube (0.9×0.5×0.01), CollisionAPI, visibility=invisible | Dedicated board collision surface |\n| `/World/QuadrantBoard/board_collision_plane` | Bind `/GripFrictionMaterial` | Prevent cube sliding off board |\n| `Q_TL`, `Q_TR`, `Q_BL`, `Q_BR` | Apply CollisionAPI | Belt-and-suspenders (backup to collision plane) |\n| `Q_TL`, `Q_TR`, `Q_BL`, `Q_BR` | Bind `/GripFrictionMaterial` (physics purpose) | Friction on board zones |\n| `shoulder_pan_joint` | `drive:angular:physics:stiffness=10000, damping=1000, type=force` | PD controller for position tracking |\n| `shoulder_lift_joint` | Same as above | Same |\n| `elbow_joint` | Same as above | Same |\n| `wrist_1_joint` | Same as above | Same |\n| `wrist_2_joint` | Same as above | Same |\n| `wrist_3_joint` | Same as above | Same |\n| `finger_joint` | `stiffness=1000, damping=100, type=force` | Lighter PD for gripper |\n| `left_inner_knuckle_joint` | Same as above | Same |\n| `left_inner_finger_joint` | Same as above | Same |\n| `right_outer_knuckle_joint` | Same as above | Same |\n| `right_inner_knuckle_joint` | Same as above | Same |\n| `right_inner_finger_joint` | Same as above | Same |\n| `/OmniKit_Viewport_LightRig/Lights/DomeLight` | Create if missing, set intensity=1.0, exposure=9.0, colorTemp=6150K | Match training lighting |\n| `/OmniKit_Viewport_LightRig/Lights/DistantLight` | Create if missing, set intensity=1.0, exposure=10.0, colorTemp=7250K, angle=0.53 | Match training lighting |\n| `/BlackGrid/SphereLight` | Set visibility=invisible | Already in scene, kept invisible |\n\n---\n\n## Appendix B: Deployment Commands\n\n```bash\n# Terminal 1: Launch policy bridge\ncd /data/tvp_ws/rlearning_ws\nsource /opt/ros/humble/setup.bash\nsource /data/tvp_ws/ros/ros2/tvp_auto_data_collection_ws/install/setup.bash\nsource install/setup.bash\nros2 launch rosetta ur5e_policy_bridge.launch.py \\\n    actions_per_chunk:=50 \\\n    ema_alpha:=1.0 \\\n    chunk_size_threshold:=0.3\n\n# Terminal 2: Trigger policy run\nros2 action send_goal /run_policy rosetta_interfaces/action/RunPolicy \"{}\"\n```\n\n**Recommended launch params:**\n- `actions_per_chunk=50` (of chunk_size=100 — use first half of each chunk)\n- `ema_alpha=1.0` (no smoothing — policy outputs are already smooth)\n- `chunk_size_threshold=0.3` (request new chunk when 30% of current remains)\n\n---\n\n## Appendix C: File Paths Quick Reference\n\n| What | Path |\n|------|------|\n| Scene setup script | `rosetta/scripts/isaacsim_scene_setup.py` |\n| Scene inspector | `rosetta/scripts/isaacsim_scene_inspect.py` |\n| Collider debugger | `rosetta/scripts/isaacsim_debug_colliders.py` |\n| Policy diagnostics | `rosetta/scripts/diagnose_policy.py` |\n| Band-aid log | `rosetta/BAND_AID_FIXES_LOG.md` |\n| This document | `rosetta/SIM2SIM_DEBUGGING_JOURNAL.md` |\n| Policy checkpoint | `outputs/act_ur5e_pnp_145ep_200k_kl01_dec1/checkpoints/200000/pretrained_model/` |\n| Normalizer (patched) | `...pretrained_model/policy_preprocessor_step_3_normalizer_processor.safetensors` |\n| Dataset | `data/lerobot_dataset/ur5e_pnp_full_v2/` |\n| Policy bridge node | `rosetta/rosetta/policy_bridge_node.py` |\n| Joint state adapter | `rosetta/rosetta/action_to_jointstate_adapter.py` |\n| Training contract | `rosetta/contracts/ur5e_robotiq_pnp.yaml` |\n| Launch file | `rosetta/launch/ur5e_policy_bridge.launch.py` |\n| USD scene | `ur5e_robotiq_gripper_adc_cell_with_camera_lerobot_inference_v1.usd` |\n",
      "tags": [
        "learning",
        "sim2sim",
        "imitation"
      ],
      "projectId": "c7szb5bi",
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "note",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2026-04-13T18:32:51.834Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-04-13T18:33:51.685Z",
      "attachments": [],
      "links": []
    },
    {
      "id": "6ufy24lf",
      "title": "SIm2Sim & ADC - Scene Inspector Script",
      "content": "\"\"\"\nIsaac Sim Scene Inspector — Full Dump\n======================================\nRun this in Isaac Sim's Script Editor (Window → Script Editor).\n\nPrints a complete snapshot of your scene:\n  • All top-level prims and their types\n  • Robot joint tree with current positions\n  • Cube position, size, mass, materials\n  • Camera prims: position, orientation, resolution\n  • Ground/table geometry\n  • Physics scene settings (gravity, solver, timestep)\n  • Material bindings on key objects\n  • Any prim whose name contains common keywords (board, quadrant, zone, target, etc.)\n\nOutput saved to /tmp/isaacsim_scene_inspect.txt\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom pxr import Usd, UsdGeom, UsdPhysics, UsdShade, Gf, Sdf\nimport math\n\nstage = omni.usd.get_context().get_stage()\nlines = []\n\ndef log(msg=\"\"):\n    print(msg)\n    lines.append(msg)\n\ndef fmt_vec3(v):\n    if v is None:\n        return \"None\"\n    return f\"({v[0]:.4f}, {v[1]:.4f}, {v[2]:.4f})\"\n\ndef get_world_transform(prim):\n    \"\"\"Get world-space translation and rotation for a prim.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        xformable = UsdGeom.Xformable(prim)\n        world_mtx = xformable.ComputeLocalToWorldTransform(Usd.TimeCode.Default())\n        translate = world_mtx.ExtractTranslation()\n        # Extract rotation as euler (degrees)\n        rot = world_mtx.ExtractRotation()\n        euler = rot.IsIdentity() and (0, 0, 0) or (\n            rot.GetAngle() * rot.GetAxis()[0] if rot.GetAxis() else 0,\n            rot.GetAngle() * rot.GetAxis()[1] if rot.GetAxis() else 0,\n            rot.GetAngle() * rot.GetAxis()[2] if rot.GetAxis() else 0,\n        )\n        return translate, rot\n    except Exception:\n        return None, None\n\ndef get_local_xform(prim):\n    \"\"\"Get local translation, rotation, scale.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        xformable = UsdGeom.Xformable(prim)\n        ops = xformable.GetOrderedXformOps()\n        translate = scale = None\n        rotate = None\n        for op in ops:\n            if op.GetOpType() == UsdGeom.XformOp.TypeTranslate:\n                translate = op.Get()\n            elif op.GetOpType() == UsdGeom.XformOp.TypeScale:\n                scale = op.Get()\n            elif \"orient\" in op.GetOpName().lower() or \"rot\" in op.GetOpName().lower():\n                rotate = op.Get()\n        return translate, rotate, scale\n    except Exception:\n        return None, None, None\n\n\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"=\" * 70)\nlog(\"ISAAC SIM SCENE INSPECTOR — FULL DUMP\")\nlog(\"=\" * 70)\n\n# ============================================================\n# 1. STAGE INFO\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- STAGE INFO ---\")\nlog(f\"  Root layer:    {stage.GetRootLayer().identifier}\")\nup_axis = UsdGeom.GetStageUpAxis(stage)\nmeters = UsdGeom.GetStageMetersPerUnit(stage)\nlog(f\"  Up axis:       {up_axis}\")\nlog(f\"  Meters/unit:   {meters}\")\nlog(f\"  Total prims:   {len(list(Usd.PrimRange(stage.GetPseudoRoot())))}\")\n\n# ============================================================\n# 2. TOP-LEVEL PRIMS\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- TOP-LEVEL PRIMS ---\")\nroot = stage.GetPseudoRoot()\nfor child in root.GetChildren():\n    ptype = child.GetTypeName() or \"(no type)\"\n    apis = [a.split(\":\")[-1] for a in child.GetAppliedSchemas()] if child.GetAppliedSchemas() else []\n    api_str = f\"  APIs: {', '.join(apis[:5])}\" if apis else \"\"\n    nchildren = len(child.GetChildren())\n    log(f\"  {child.GetPath()}  type={ptype}  children={nchildren}{api_str}\")\n\n# ============================================================\n# 3. RECURSIVE TREE (depth-limited)\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- SCENE TREE (depth ≤ 3) ---\")\ndef print_tree(prim, depth=0, max_depth=3):\n    if depth > max_depth:\n        return\n    indent = \"  \" + \"  │ \" * depth\n    ptype = prim.GetTypeName() or \"\"\n    type_str = f\" [{ptype}]\" if ptype else \"\"\n    log(f\"{indent}{prim.GetName()}{type_str}\")\n    for child in prim.GetChildren():\n        print_tree(child, depth + 1, max_depth)\n\nfor child in root.GetChildren():\n    print_tree(child, 0, 3)\n\n# ============================================================\n# 4. PHYSICS SCENE\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- PHYSICS SCENE ---\")\nfor prim in Usd.PrimRange(stage.GetPseudoRoot()):\n    if prim.IsA(UsdPhysics.Scene):\n        log(f\"  Path: {prim.GetPath()}\")\n        scene_api = UsdPhysics.Scene(prim)\n        grav = scene_api.GetGravityDirectionAttr().Get()\n        grav_mag = scene_api.GetGravityMagnitudeAttr().Get()\n        log(f\"  Gravity direction: {grav}\")\n        log(f\"  Gravity magnitude: {grav_mag}\")\n        # Check for PhysX scene attributes\n        for attr in prim.GetAttributes():\n            name = attr.GetName()\n            if \"timeStep\" in name or \"solver\" in name or \"bounce\" in name or \"friction\" in name:\n                log(f\"  {name} = {attr.Get()}\")\n        break\nelse:\n    log(\"  No UsdPhysics.Scene found\")\n\n# ============================================================\n# 5. CUBE DETAILS\n# ============================================================\nCUBE_CANDIDATES = [\"/Test_Cube\", \"/World/Test_Cube\", \"/World/Cube\"]\nlog(\"\\n--- CUBE ---\")\nfor cpath in CUBE_CANDIDATES:\n    cprim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(cpath)\n    if cprim and cprim.IsValid():\n        log(f\"  Path: {cpath}  type={cprim.GetTypeName()}\")\n        t, r, s = get_local_xform(cprim)\n        wt, wr = get_world_transform(cprim)\n        log(f\"  Local  translate: {fmt_vec3(t)}\")\n        log(f\"  Local  scale:     {fmt_vec3(s) if s else 'None'}\")\n        log(f\"  World  translate: {fmt_vec3(wt)}\")\n        # Size\n        if cprim.IsA(UsdGeom.Cube):\n            size_attr = UsdGeom.Cube(cprim).GetSizeAttr().Get()\n            log(f\"  Cube size attr:   {size_attr}\")\n        extent = UsdGeom.Boundable(cprim).GetExtentAttr().Get() if cprim.IsA(UsdGeom.Boundable) else None\n        if extent:\n            log(f\"  Extent:           {extent}\")\n        # Physics\n        has_rb = cprim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.RigidBodyAPI)\n        log(f\"  RigidBody:        {has_rb}\")\n        if cprim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.MassAPI):\n            m = UsdPhysics.MassAPI(cprim).GetMassAttr().Get()\n            log(f\"  Mass:             {m} kg\")\n        # Material bindings\n        bind_api = UsdShade.MaterialBindingAPI(cprim)\n        for purpose in [\"\", \"physics\"]:\n            rel = bind_api.GetDirectBinding(purpose) if not purpose else bind_api.GetDirectBinding(purpose)\n            mat = bind_api.ComputeBoundMaterial(purpose) if purpose else bind_api.ComputeBoundMaterial()\n            if mat and mat[0]:\n                log(f\"  Material ({purpose or 'render'}): {mat[0].GetPath()}\")\n        break\nelse:\n    log(\"  No cube found at any candidate path\")\n\n# ============================================================\n# 6. ROBOT DETAILS\n# ============================================================\nROBOT_PATH = \"/World/ur\"\nlog(\"\\n--- ROBOT ---\")\nrobot_prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(ROBOT_PATH)\nif robot_prim and robot_prim.IsValid():\n    log(f\"  Path: {ROBOT_PATH}  type={robot_prim.GetTypeName()}\")\n    t, r, s = get_local_xform(robot_prim)\n    wt, wr = get_world_transform(robot_prim)\n    log(f\"  Local  translate: {fmt_vec3(t)}\")\n    log(f\"  World  translate: {fmt_vec3(wt)}\")\n    log(f\"  Instanceable:     {robot_prim.IsInstanceable()}\")\n\n    # List all joints and their current positions\n    log(f\"\\n  Joints:\")\n    for desc in Usd.PrimRange(robot_prim):\n        if desc.IsA(UsdPhysics.Joint) or desc.GetTypeName() in (\"PhysicsRevoluteJoint\", \"PhysicsFixedJoint\", \"PhysicsPrismaticJoint\"):\n            joint_type = desc.GetTypeName()\n            # Try to get joint position/limits\n            lower = upper = pos = None\n            for attr in desc.GetAttributes():\n                name = attr.GetName()\n                if \"lower\" in name.lower():\n                    lower = attr.Get()\n                elif \"upper\" in name.lower():\n                    upper = attr.Get()\n                elif name == \"state:angular:physics:position\" or name == \"state:linear:physics:position\":\n                    pos = attr.Get()\n            log(f\"    {desc.GetName():45s}  type={joint_type}  pos={pos}  limits=[{lower}, {upper}]\")\n\n    # List all links\n    log(f\"\\n  Links (direct children with Xform type):\")\n    link_count = 0\n    for child in Usd.PrimRange(robot_prim):\n        if child.GetTypeName() in (\"Xform\", \"\") and child.GetParent().GetPath() == robot_prim.GetPath():\n            wt2, _ = get_world_transform(child)\n            log(f\"    {child.GetName():45s}  world_pos={fmt_vec3(wt2)}\")\n            link_count += 1\n    log(f\"  Total direct child links: {link_count}\")\nelse:\n    log(f\"  Robot not found at {ROBOT_PATH}\")\n\n# ============================================================\n# 7. CAMERAS\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- CAMERAS ---\")\ncam_count = 0\nfor prim in Usd.PrimRange(stage.GetPseudoRoot()):\n    if prim.IsA(UsdGeom.Camera):\n        cam_count += 1\n        path_str = str(prim.GetPath())\n        # Skip editor cameras\n        if \"OmniverseKit\" in path_str:\n            continue\n        wt, wr = get_world_transform(prim)\n        cam = UsdGeom.Camera(prim)\n        fl = cam.GetFocalLengthAttr().Get()\n        ha = cam.GetHorizontalApertureAttr().Get()\n        va = cam.GetVerticalApertureAttr().Get()\n        clip = cam.GetClippingRangeAttr().Get()\n        # Local xform\n        t, r, s = get_local_xform(prim)\n        log(f\"  {prim.GetPath()}\")\n        log(f\"    Local pos:      {t}\")\n        log(f\"    Local orient:   {r}\")\n        log(f\"    Local scale:    {s}\")\n        log(f\"    World pos:      {fmt_vec3(wt)}\")\n        log(f\"    Focal length:   {fl}\")\n        log(f\"    H aperture:     {ha}\")\n        log(f\"    V aperture:     {va}\")\n        log(f\"    Clip range:     {clip}\")\nif cam_count == 0:\n    log(\"  No UsdGeom.Camera prims found\")\n\n# ============================================================\n# 7b. LIGHTS — full property dump for setup script reproduction\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- LIGHTS (full property dump) ---\")\nlight_count = 0\nfor prim in Usd.PrimRange(stage.GetPseudoRoot()):\n    ptype = prim.GetTypeName()\n    if \"Light\" in ptype:\n        light_count += 1\n        log(f\"  {prim.GetPath()}  type={ptype}\")\n\n        # Xform\n        t, r, s = get_local_xform(prim)\n        wt, _ = get_world_transform(prim)\n        log(f\"    Local pos:    {t}\")\n        log(f\"    Local orient: {r}\")\n        log(f\"    Local scale:  {s}\")\n        log(f\"    World pos:    {fmt_vec3(wt)}\")\n\n        # Visibility\n        vis_attr = prim.GetAttribute(\"visibility\")\n        if vis_attr and vis_attr.IsValid():\n            log(f\"    visibility = {vis_attr.Get()}\")\n\n        # Dump ALL authored attributes (captures everything — intensity, color,\n        # radius, exposure, temperature, shaping, etc.)\n        log(f\"    --- Authored attributes ---\")\n        for attr in prim.GetAttributes():\n            if attr.IsAuthored():\n                name = attr.GetName()\n                # Skip xformOp attrs (already printed above) and internal ones\n                if name.startswith(\"xformOp\") or name.startswith(\"xformOpOrder\"):\n                    continue\n                val = attr.Get()\n                log(f\"    {name} = {val}\")\n\n        # Also dump non-authored defaults for key light properties\n        # (so we know what Isaac Sim defaults are being used)\n        log(f\"    --- Key defaults (even if not authored) ---\")\n        for attr_name in [\n            \"inputs:intensity\", \"inputs:color\", \"inputs:radius\",\n            \"inputs:exposure\", \"inputs:diffuse\", \"inputs:specular\",\n            \"inputs:enableColorTemperature\", \"inputs:colorTemperature\",\n            \"inputs:width\", \"inputs:height\", \"inputs:length\", \"inputs:angle\",\n            \"inputs:shaping:cone:angle\", \"inputs:shaping:cone:softness\",\n            \"inputs:shaping:focus\", \"inputs:shaping:focusTint\",\n            \"treatAsPoint\",\n        ]:\n            attr = prim.GetAttribute(attr_name)\n            if attr and attr.IsValid():\n                val = attr.Get()\n                authored = \"authored\" if attr.IsAuthored() else \"default\"\n                log(f\"    {attr_name} = {val}  [{authored}]\")\n\n        log(\"\")\n\nif light_count == 0:\n    log(\"  No lights found in scene\")\n\n# ============================================================\n# 8. KEYWORD SEARCH — find quadrant board, zones, targets, etc.\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- KEYWORD SEARCH (board, quadrant, zone, target, table, ground, plane, bin, tray) ---\")\nKEYWORDS = [\"board\", \"quadrant\", \"zone\", \"target\", \"table\", \"ground\", \"plane\", \"bin\", \"tray\", \"surface\", \"desk\", \"mat\", \"region\"]\nfound_any = False\nfor prim in Usd.PrimRange(stage.GetPseudoRoot()):\n    name_lower = prim.GetName().lower()\n    for kw in KEYWORDS:\n        if kw in name_lower:\n            found_any = True\n            ptype = prim.GetTypeName() or \"(no type)\"\n            wt, _ = get_world_transform(prim)\n            t, r, s = get_local_xform(prim)\n            log(f\"  {prim.GetPath()}  type={ptype}\")\n            log(f\"    World pos:  {fmt_vec3(wt)}\")\n            log(f\"    Local pos:  {fmt_vec3(t)}\")\n            log(f\"    Scale:      {fmt_vec3(s) if s else 'None'}\")\n            # Check for children (sub-zones?)\n            children = list(prim.GetChildren())\n            if children:\n                log(f\"    Children ({len(children)}):\")\n                for ch in children[:10]:\n                    chwt, _ = get_world_transform(ch)\n                    log(f\"      {ch.GetName():35s}  type={ch.GetTypeName()}  world_pos={fmt_vec3(chwt)}\")\n                if len(children) > 10:\n                    log(f\"      ... and {len(children)-10} more\")\n            break  # don't double-log same prim for multiple keyword matches\nif not found_any:\n    log(\"  No prims found matching any keyword\")\n\n# ============================================================\n# 9. ALL RIGID BODIES (non-robot)\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- ALL RIGID BODIES (outside robot) ---\")\nfor prim in Usd.PrimRange(stage.GetPseudoRoot()):\n    if prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.RigidBodyAPI) and not str(prim.GetPath()).startswith(ROBOT_PATH):\n        wt, _ = get_world_transform(prim)\n        mass_str = \"\"\n        if prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.MassAPI):\n            m = UsdPhysics.MassAPI(prim).GetMassAttr().Get()\n            mass_str = f\"  mass={m}\"\n        log(f\"  {prim.GetPath()}  type={prim.GetTypeName()}  world_pos={fmt_vec3(wt)}{mass_str}\")\n\n# ============================================================\n# 10. ALL MATERIALS\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- ALL MATERIALS ---\")\nfor prim in Usd.PrimRange(stage.GetPseudoRoot()):\n    if prim.IsA(UsdShade.Material):\n        has_phys = prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.MaterialAPI)\n        phys_str = \"\"\n        if has_phys:\n            pm = UsdPhysics.MaterialAPI(prim)\n            sf = pm.GetStaticFrictionAttr().Get()\n            df = pm.GetDynamicFrictionAttr().Get()\n            rest = pm.GetRestitutionAttr().Get()\n            phys_str = f\"  sf={sf} df={df} restitution={rest}\"\n        log(f\"  {prim.GetPath()}  physics={has_phys}{phys_str}\")\n\n# ============================================================\n# SAVE\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 70)\nlog(\"INSPECTION COMPLETE\")\nlog(\"=\" * 70)\n\npath = \"/tmp/isaacsim_scene_inspect.txt\"\ntry:\n    with open(path, \"w\") as f:\n        f.write(\"\\n\".join(lines))\n    log(f\"\\nReport saved to {path}\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print(f\"Could not save report: {e}\")\n",
      "tags": [
        "learning",
        "sim2sim",
        "imitation"
      ],
      "projectId": "c7szb5bi",
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "note",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2026-04-13T18:34:12.795Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-04-13T18:43:45.670Z",
      "attachments": [],
      "links": []
    },
    {
      "id": "z1uxeor0",
      "title": "SIm2Sim & ADC - Scene Setup Script",
      "content": "\"\"\"\nIsaac Sim Scene Setup — All-in-One (Idempotent)\n================================================\nRun this in Isaac Sim's Script Editor (Window → Script Editor).\n\nThis single script does everything needed to prepare the UR5e + Robotiq 85\npick-and-place scene for sim2sim policy deployment. It is IDEMPOTENT — safe\nto run multiple times. It will skip anything already done.\n\nWhat it does:\n  1. INSPECT        — Prints scene structure (cube, robot, board, colliders, materials)\n  2. CUBE           — Sets cube mass, RigidBody, CollisionAPI\n  3. INSTANCING     — Disables USD instancing on robot so finger links are editable\n  4. COLLIDERS      — Adds box colliders to 4 gripper finger links (if missing)\n  5. FRICTION       — Creates high-friction physics material and binds to fingers + cube\n  6. QUADRANT BOARD — Collision plane under board + CollisionAPI on Q_ zones + friction\n  6b. JOINT DRIVES  — Sets stiffness + damping on all UR5e + gripper articulation drives\n  6c. LIGHTING      — Enforces DomeLight + DistantLight settings to match training\n  7. VERIFY         — Confirms everything is set up correctly\n\nReport saved to /tmp/isaacsim_scene_setup_report.txt\n\nNOTE: This script does NOT change the cube's visual appearance.\n      If a previous script turned the cube red, fix it manually:\n        Select /Test_Cube → Property → Material → assign your original material\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom pxr import Usd, UsdGeom, UsdShade, UsdPhysics, UsdLux, Gf, Sdf\n\nstage = omni.usd.get_context().get_stage()\nlines = []\nissues = []   # track things that failed\nskipped = []  # track things already done\n\ndef log(msg):\n    print(msg)\n    lines.append(msg)\n\ndef save_report():\n    path = \"/tmp/isaacsim_scene_setup_report.txt\"\n    try:\n        with open(path, \"w\") as f:\n            f.write(\"\\n\".join(lines))\n        log(f\"\\nReport saved to {path}\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Could not save report: {e}\")\n\n# ============================================================\n# CONFIG — edit these if your scene paths differ\n# ============================================================\nCUBE_PATH = \"/Test_Cube\"\nROBOT_PATH = \"/World/ur\"\nCUBE_MASS_KG = 0.03\n\nFINGER_LINKS = [\n    \"/World/ur/robotiq_85_left_finger_tip_link\",\n    \"/World/ur/robotiq_85_right_finger_tip_link\",\n    \"/World/ur/robotiq_85_left_inner_knuckle_link\",\n    \"/World/ur/robotiq_85_right_inner_knuckle_link\",\n]\n\n# Collider geometry: (path_suffix, half-extents as scale, offset)\nCOLLIDER_CONFIGS = [\n    (\"robotiq_85_left_finger_tip_link\",\n     Gf.Vec3f(0.02, 0.03, 0.015), Gf.Vec3f(0.0, 0.015, 0.0)),\n    (\"robotiq_85_right_finger_tip_link\",\n     Gf.Vec3f(0.02, 0.03, 0.015), Gf.Vec3f(0.0, -0.015, 0.0)),\n    (\"robotiq_85_left_inner_knuckle_link\",\n     Gf.Vec3f(0.015, 0.04, 0.015), Gf.Vec3f(0.0, 0.01, 0.0)),\n    (\"robotiq_85_right_inner_knuckle_link\",\n     Gf.Vec3f(0.015, 0.04, 0.015), Gf.Vec3f(0.0, -0.01, 0.0)),\n]\n\nFRICTION_MAT_PATH = \"/GripFrictionMaterial\"\nFRICTION_STATIC = 2.0\nFRICTION_DYNAMIC = 2.0\nFRICTION_RESTITUTION = 0.0\n\nQUADRANT_BOARD_PATH = \"/World/QuadrantBoard/QuadrantBoard\"\nQUADRANT_ZONES = [\n    f\"{QUADRANT_BOARD_PATH}/Q_TL\",\n    f\"{QUADRANT_BOARD_PATH}/Q_TR\",\n    f\"{QUADRANT_BOARD_PATH}/Q_BL\",\n    f\"{QUADRANT_BOARD_PATH}/Q_BR\",\n]\n# Dedicated invisible collision plane that sits at the board surface.\n# The Q_ zones are visual cubes with scale=(0.4, 0.2, 0.005) at Z≈0.0025,\n# so the top surface is at Z≈0.005. We place a thin collision box just below\n# that covers the entire board footprint (0.8 × 0.4 m from the four zones).\nBOARD_COLLIDER_PATH = \"/World/QuadrantBoard/board_collision_plane\"\nBOARD_COLLIDER_HEIGHT = 0.005   # top surface Z — matches Q_ zones\nBOARD_COLLIDER_SIZE = (0.9, 0.5, 0.01)  # slightly larger than visual board\n\n# Joint drive parameters — UR5e arm joints need high stiffness/damping to\n# hold poses under gravity + payload. Gripper joints are lighter.\n# These match typical IsaacSim UR5e defaults for position-controlled joints.\nUR5E_ARM_JOINTS = [\n    \"shoulder_pan_joint\",\n    \"shoulder_lift_joint\",\n    \"elbow_joint\",\n    \"wrist_1_joint\",\n    \"wrist_2_joint\",\n    \"wrist_3_joint\",\n]\nGRIPPER_JOINTS = [\n    \"finger_joint\",\n    \"left_inner_knuckle_joint\",\n    \"left_inner_finger_joint\",\n    \"right_outer_knuckle_joint\",\n    \"right_inner_knuckle_joint\",\n    \"right_inner_finger_joint\",\n]\n# Stiffness and damping values\nARM_DRIVE_STIFFNESS = 10000.0    # N·m/rad — strong enough to hold arm poses\nARM_DRIVE_DAMPING = 1000.0       # N·m·s/rad\nGRIPPER_DRIVE_STIFFNESS = 1000.0 # lighter for gripper\nGRIPPER_DRIVE_DAMPING = 100.0\n\n# Lighting config — captured from inspector on the golden scene.\n# The scene uses a Viewport Light Rig (DomeLight + DistantLight).\n# The original SphereLight under /BlackGrid is intentionally invisible.\nLIGHT_CONFIGS = [\n    {\n        \"path\": \"/BlackGrid/SphereLight\",\n        \"type\": \"SphereLight\",\n        \"create\": False,  # already exists in default scene\n        \"attrs\": {\n            \"visibility\": \"invisible\",\n            \"inputs:intensity\": 1000000.0,\n            \"inputs:radius\": 0.3,\n            \"inputs:shaping:cone:angle\": 180.0,\n        },\n    },\n    {\n        \"path\": \"/OmniKit_Viewport_LightRig/Lights/DomeLight\",\n        \"type\": \"DomeLight\",\n        \"create\": True,  # may not exist if light rig wasn't created\n        \"attrs\": {\n            \"visibility\": \"inherited\",\n            \"inputs:intensity\": 1.0,\n            \"inputs:exposure\": 9.0,\n            \"inputs:enableColorTemperature\": True,\n            \"inputs:colorTemperature\": 6150.0,\n            \"inputs:shaping:cone:angle\": 180.0,\n            \"inputs:texture:format\": \"latlong\",\n        },\n    },\n    {\n        \"path\": \"/OmniKit_Viewport_LightRig/Lights/DistantLight\",\n        \"type\": \"DistantLight\",\n        \"create\": True,\n        \"attrs\": {\n            \"visibility\": \"inherited\",\n            \"inputs:intensity\": 1.0,\n            \"inputs:exposure\": 10.0,\n            \"inputs:angle\": 0.53,\n            \"inputs:enableColorTemperature\": True,\n            \"inputs:colorTemperature\": 7250.0,\n            \"inputs:shaping:cone:angle\": 180.0,\n        },\n    },\n]\n# Xform for the light rig container + individual lights\nLIGHT_RIG_PATH = \"/OmniKit_Viewport_LightRig\"\nLIGHT_RIG_LIGHTS_PATH = \"/OmniKit_Viewport_LightRig/Lights\"\n# Positions/orientations (translate, rotate) for the rig lights\nLIGHT_XFORMS = {\n    \"/OmniKit_Viewport_LightRig/Lights/DomeLight\": {\n        \"translate\": Gf.Vec3d(0, 0, 305),\n        \"rotate\": Gf.Vec3d(0, 0, 62.3),\n    },\n    \"/OmniKit_Viewport_LightRig/Lights/DistantLight\": {\n        \"translate\": Gf.Vec3d(0, 0, 305),\n        \"rotate\": Gf.Vec3d(55, 0, 135),\n    },\n}\n\n\nlog(\"=\" * 60)\nlog(\"ISAAC SIM SCENE SETUP — ALL-IN-ONE\")\nlog(\"=\" * 60)\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# STEP 1: INSPECT — show what's in the scene\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- STEP 1: SCENE INSPECTION ---\")\n\ncube_prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(CUBE_PATH)\nif cube_prim and cube_prim.IsValid():\n    has_rb = cube_prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.RigidBodyAPI)\n    has_mass = cube_prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.MassAPI)\n    mass_val = \"NOT SET\"\n    if has_mass:\n        mass_api = UsdPhysics.MassAPI(cube_prim)\n        m = mass_api.GetMassAttr().Get()\n        mass_val = f\"{m} kg\" if m else \"NOT SET (attr exists but empty)\"\n    log(f\"  Cube: {CUBE_PATH}  RigidBody={has_rb}  mass={mass_val}\")\nelse:\n    log(f\"  WARNING: Cube not found at {CUBE_PATH}\")\n    issues.append(f\"Cube not found at {CUBE_PATH}\")\n\nrobot_prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(ROBOT_PATH)\nif robot_prim and robot_prim.IsValid():\n    is_instanceable = robot_prim.IsInstanceable()\n    log(f\"  Robot: {ROBOT_PATH}  instanceable={is_instanceable}\")\nelse:\n    log(f\"  WARNING: Robot not found at {ROBOT_PATH}\")\n    issues.append(f\"Robot not found at {ROBOT_PATH}\")\n\nfor link in FINGER_LINKS:\n    p = stage.GetPrimAtPath(link)\n    exists = p and p.IsValid()\n    is_proxy = False\n    if exists:\n        try:\n            is_proxy = p.IsInstanceProxy()\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n    log(f\"  Finger: {link.split('/')[-1]:45s}  exists={exists}  instance_proxy={is_proxy}\")\n\n# QuadrantBoard\nboard_prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(QUADRANT_BOARD_PATH)\nif board_prim and board_prim.IsValid():\n    log(f\"  QuadrantBoard: {QUADRANT_BOARD_PATH}\")\n    for qpath in QUADRANT_ZONES:\n        qp = stage.GetPrimAtPath(qpath)\n        if qp and qp.IsValid():\n            has_col = qp.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI)\n            # Read local xform for position/size\n            xformable = UsdGeom.Xformable(qp)\n            ops = xformable.GetOrderedXformOps()\n            t_val = s_val = None\n            for op in ops:\n                if op.GetOpType() == UsdGeom.XformOp.TypeTranslate:\n                    t_val = op.Get()\n                elif op.GetOpType() == UsdGeom.XformOp.TypeScale:\n                    s_val = op.Get()\n            size_str = \"\"\n            if qp.IsA(UsdGeom.Cube):\n                sz = UsdGeom.Cube(qp).GetSizeAttr().Get()\n                size_str = f\"  size={sz}\"\n            log(f\"    {qpath.split('/')[-1]:8s}  collision={has_col}  pos={t_val}  scale={s_val}{size_str}\")\n        else:\n            log(f\"    {qpath.split('/')[-1]:8s}  NOT FOUND\")\n            issues.append(f\"Quadrant zone not found: {qpath}\")\nelse:\n    log(f\"  WARNING: QuadrantBoard not found at {QUADRANT_BOARD_PATH}\")\n    issues.append(f\"QuadrantBoard not found at {QUADRANT_BOARD_PATH}\")\n\n# Lights\nlog(\"\")\nlog(\"  --- Lights ---\")\nlight_count = 0\nfor prim in Usd.PrimRange(stage.GetPseudoRoot()):\n    ptype = prim.GetTypeName()\n    if \"Light\" in ptype:\n        light_count += 1\n        # Read local xform\n        xf = UsdGeom.Xformable(prim)\n        xf_ops = xf.GetOrderedXformOps()\n        lt = ls = None\n        for op in xf_ops:\n            if op.GetOpType() == UsdGeom.XformOp.TypeTranslate:\n                lt = op.Get()\n            elif op.GetOpType() == UsdGeom.XformOp.TypeScale:\n                ls = op.Get()\n        log(f\"  {prim.GetPath()}  type={ptype}\")\n        log(f\"    Local pos:  {lt}\")\n        log(f\"    Scale:      {ls}\")\n        # Read common light attributes\n        for attr_name in [\"inputs:intensity\", \"inputs:color\", \"inputs:radius\",\n                          \"inputs:width\", \"inputs:height\", \"inputs:length\",\n                          \"inputs:angle\", \"inputs:exposure\",\n                          \"inputs:enableColorTemperature\", \"inputs:colorTemperature\",\n                          \"inputs:diffuse\", \"inputs:specular\",\n                          \"treatAsPoint\", \"inputs:shaping:cone:angle\",\n                          \"inputs:shaping:cone:softness\"]:\n            attr = prim.GetAttribute(attr_name)\n            if attr and attr.IsValid():\n                val = attr.Get()\n                if val is not None:\n                    log(f\"    {attr_name} = {val}\")\nif light_count == 0:\n    log(\"  No lights found in scene\")\n\n# Cameras (local xform since world transforms need sim running)\nlog(\"\")\nlog(\"  --- Cameras ---\")\nfor prim in Usd.PrimRange(stage.GetPseudoRoot()):\n    if prim.IsA(UsdGeom.Camera):\n        path_str = str(prim.GetPath())\n        # Skip editor cameras\n        if \"OmniverseKit\" in path_str:\n            continue\n        cam = UsdGeom.Camera(prim)\n        fl = cam.GetFocalLengthAttr().Get()\n        ha = cam.GetHorizontalApertureAttr().Get()\n        va = cam.GetVerticalApertureAttr().Get()\n        clip = cam.GetClippingRangeAttr().Get()\n        # Local xform\n        xf = UsdGeom.Xformable(prim)\n        xf_ops = xf.GetOrderedXformOps()\n        ct = cr = None\n        for op in xf_ops:\n            if op.GetOpType() == UsdGeom.XformOp.TypeTranslate:\n                ct = op.Get()\n            elif \"orient\" in op.GetOpName().lower() or \"rot\" in op.GetOpName().lower():\n                cr = op.Get()\n        log(f\"  {prim.GetPath()}\")\n        log(f\"    Local pos:      {ct}\")\n        log(f\"    Local orient:   {cr}\")\n        log(f\"    Focal length:   {fl}\")\n        log(f\"    H aperture:     {ha}\")\n        log(f\"    V aperture:     {va}\")\n        log(f\"    Clip range:     {clip}\")\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# STEP 2: CUBE MASS — set to 0.03 kg\n# ============================================================\nlog(f\"\\n--- STEP 2: CUBE PHYSICS ({CUBE_MASS_KG} kg) ---\")\n\nif cube_prim and cube_prim.IsValid():\n    try:\n        # Ensure RigidBodyAPI\n        if not cube_prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.RigidBodyAPI):\n            UsdPhysics.RigidBodyAPI.Apply(cube_prim)\n            log(\"  Applied RigidBodyAPI to cube\")\n\n        # Ensure CollisionAPI — WITHOUT THIS, NOTHING COLLIDES WITH THE CUBE\n        if not cube_prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI):\n            UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI.Apply(cube_prim)\n            log(\"  Applied CollisionAPI to cube\")\n        else:\n            log(\"  Cube already has CollisionAPI\")\n\n        # Ensure MassAPI and set mass\n        if not cube_prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.MassAPI):\n            UsdPhysics.MassAPI.Apply(cube_prim)\n\n        mass_api = UsdPhysics.MassAPI(cube_prim)\n        current_mass = mass_api.GetMassAttr().Get()\n\n        if current_mass and abs(current_mass - CUBE_MASS_KG) < 1e-6:\n            log(f\"  ALREADY SET: mass = {CUBE_MASS_KG} kg\")\n            skipped.append(\"Cube mass\")\n        else:\n            mass_api.GetMassAttr().Set(CUBE_MASS_KG)\n            log(f\"  SET: mass {current_mass} → {CUBE_MASS_KG} kg\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        log(f\"  FAILED: {e}\")\n        issues.append(f\"Cube mass: {e}\")\nelse:\n    log(\"  SKIPPED: cube not found\")\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# STEP 3: DISABLE INSTANCING on robot\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- STEP 3: DISABLE USD INSTANCING ---\")\n\nuninstanced_count = 0\ntry:\n    robot_prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(ROBOT_PATH)\n    if robot_prim and robot_prim.IsValid():\n        # Check the robot prim itself\n        if robot_prim.IsInstanceable():\n            robot_prim.SetInstanceable(False)\n            log(f\"  UNINSTANCED: {ROBOT_PATH}\")\n            uninstanced_count += 1\n\n        # Also check all descendants\n        for desc in Usd.PrimRange(robot_prim):\n            if desc.IsInstanceable():\n                desc.SetInstanceable(False)\n                log(f\"  UNINSTANCED: {desc.GetPath()}\")\n                uninstanced_count += 1\n\n    if uninstanced_count == 0:\n        log(\"  ALREADY DONE: no instanceable prims found (good)\")\n        skipped.append(\"Instancing\")\n    else:\n        log(f\"  Disabled instancing on {uninstanced_count} prim(s)\")\nexcept Exception as e:\n    log(f\"  FAILED: {e}\")\n    issues.append(f\"Instancing: {e}\")\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# STEP 4: CREATE FRICTION MATERIAL\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- STEP 4: FRICTION MATERIAL ---\")\n\nfriction_mat = None\ntry:\n    mat_prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(FRICTION_MAT_PATH)\n    if mat_prim and mat_prim.IsValid() and mat_prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.MaterialAPI):\n        # Already exists — just read it\n        mat_api = UsdPhysics.MaterialAPI(mat_prim)\n        sf = mat_api.GetStaticFrictionAttr().Get()\n        df = mat_api.GetDynamicFrictionAttr().Get()\n        log(f\"  ALREADY EXISTS: {FRICTION_MAT_PATH} (sf={sf}, df={df})\")\n        friction_mat = UsdShade.Material(mat_prim)\n        skipped.append(\"Friction material\")\n    else:\n        # Create new material\n        friction_mat = UsdShade.Material.Define(stage, FRICTION_MAT_PATH)\n        mat_api = UsdPhysics.MaterialAPI.Apply(friction_mat.GetPrim())\n        mat_api.CreateStaticFrictionAttr(FRICTION_STATIC)\n        mat_api.CreateDynamicFrictionAttr(FRICTION_DYNAMIC)\n        mat_api.CreateRestitutionAttr(FRICTION_RESTITUTION)\n        log(f\"  CREATED: {FRICTION_MAT_PATH}\")\n        log(f\"    static_friction={FRICTION_STATIC}\")\n        log(f\"    dynamic_friction={FRICTION_DYNAMIC}\")\n        log(f\"    restitution={FRICTION_RESTITUTION}\")\n\n    # Also check for the old /Cubephymaterial and report it\n    old_mat = stage.GetPrimAtPath(\"/Cubephymaterial\")\n    if old_mat and old_mat.IsValid():\n        log(f\"  NOTE: Old /Cubephymaterial also exists in scene (not modified)\")\n\nexcept Exception as e:\n    log(f\"  FAILED: {e}\")\n    issues.append(f\"Friction material: {e}\")\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# STEP 5: ADD FINGER COLLIDERS\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- STEP 5: FINGER COLLIDERS ---\")\n\ncreated_colliders = []\nfor link_name, scale, offset in COLLIDER_CONFIGS:\n    link_path = f\"{ROBOT_PATH}/{link_name}\"\n\n    # Try these paths in order of preference\n    candidate_paths = [\n        f\"{link_path}/collisions/pad_collider\",  # inside existing /collisions Xform\n        f\"{link_path}/pad_collider\",              # direct child of link\n    ]\n\n    # Check if any collider already exists at any candidate path\n    already_exists = False\n    for cpath in candidate_paths:\n        existing = stage.GetPrimAtPath(cpath)\n        if existing and existing.IsValid():\n            log(f\"  ALREADY EXISTS: {cpath}\")\n            created_colliders.append(cpath)\n            already_exists = True\n            skipped.append(f\"Collider {link_name}\")\n            break\n\n    if already_exists:\n        continue\n\n    # Try to create at each candidate path\n    created = False\n    for cpath in candidate_paths:\n        try:\n            geom = UsdGeom.Cube.Define(stage, cpath)\n            geom.CreateSizeAttr(1.0)\n            geom.CreateExtentAttr([Gf.Vec3f(-0.5), Gf.Vec3f(0.5)])\n            geom.AddTranslateOp().Set(offset)\n            geom.AddScaleOp().Set(scale)\n            # Hide from rendering via visibility (NOT purpose=guide, which\n            # makes PhysX ignore the prim entirely!)\n            UsdGeom.Imageable(geom.GetPrim()).GetVisibilityAttr().Set(\"invisible\")\n            UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI.Apply(geom.GetPrim())\n            log(f\"  CREATED: {cpath}\")\n            created_colliders.append(cpath)\n            created = True\n            break\n        except Exception as e:\n            log(f\"  Cannot create at {cpath}: {e}\")\n            continue\n\n    if not created:\n        log(f\"  FAILED: could not create collider for {link_name}\")\n        issues.append(f\"Collider for {link_name}\")\n\n# Repair pass: fix any existing colliders that have purpose=\"guide\" from\n# a previous run — purpose=\"guide\" makes PhysX skip them entirely!\nfor cpath in created_colliders:\n    cp = stage.GetPrimAtPath(cpath)\n    if cp and cp.IsValid():\n        purpose_attr = UsdGeom.Imageable(cp).GetPurposeAttr()\n        if purpose_attr and purpose_attr.Get() == \"guide\":\n            purpose_attr.Set(\"default\")\n            UsdGeom.Imageable(cp).GetVisibilityAttr().Set(\"invisible\")\n            log(f\"  REPAIRED: {cpath} purpose guide→default + visibility=invisible\")\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# STEP 6: BIND FRICTION MATERIAL to colliders + cube\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- STEP 6: BIND FRICTION MATERIAL ---\")\n\nif friction_mat is not None:\n    # Bind to all finger colliders\n    for cpath in created_colliders:\n        try:\n            prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(cpath)\n            if prim and prim.IsValid():\n                bind_api = UsdShade.MaterialBindingAPI.Apply(prim)\n                # Use \"physics\" purpose so we don't override visual materials\n                bind_api.Bind(friction_mat, UsdShade.Tokens.weakerThanDescendants, \"physics\")\n                log(f\"  BOUND: {cpath} → {FRICTION_MAT_PATH} (physics)\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            log(f\"  FAILED on {cpath}: {e}\")\n            issues.append(f\"Bind material to {cpath}: {e}\")\n\n    # Bind to cube too\n    if cube_prim and cube_prim.IsValid():\n        try:\n            bind_api = UsdShade.MaterialBindingAPI.Apply(cube_prim)\n            bind_api.Bind(friction_mat, UsdShade.Tokens.weakerThanDescendants, \"physics\")\n            log(f\"  BOUND: {CUBE_PATH} → {FRICTION_MAT_PATH} (physics)\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            log(f\"  FAILED on cube: {e}\")\n            issues.append(f\"Bind material to cube: {e}\")\nelse:\n    log(\"  SKIPPED: no friction material available\")\n    issues.append(\"No friction material to bind\")\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# STEP 6b: QUADRANT BOARD — collision plane + friction on Q_ zones\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- STEP 6b: QUADRANT BOARD COLLISION ---\")\n\n# ---- A. Create a dedicated invisible collision box for the board surface ----\n# This is the PRIMARY collision mechanism. The Q_ visual cubes are too thin\n# and may not register with PhysX. A proper collision box guarantees contact.\ncol_prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(BOARD_COLLIDER_PATH)\nif col_prim and col_prim.IsValid():\n    log(f\"  ALREADY EXISTS: {BOARD_COLLIDER_PATH}\")\n    skipped.append(\"Board collision plane\")\n    # Repair: fix purpose=\"guide\" from previous run\n    purpose_attr = UsdGeom.Imageable(col_prim).GetPurposeAttr()\n    if purpose_attr and purpose_attr.Get() == \"guide\":\n        purpose_attr.Set(\"default\")\n        UsdGeom.Imageable(col_prim).GetVisibilityAttr().Set(\"invisible\")\n        log(f\"  REPAIRED: board collider purpose guide→default + visibility=invisible\")\nelse:\n    try:\n        geom = UsdGeom.Cube.Define(stage, BOARD_COLLIDER_PATH)\n        geom.CreateSizeAttr(1.0)\n        sx, sy, sz = BOARD_COLLIDER_SIZE\n        geom.AddTranslateOp().Set(Gf.Vec3d(0, 0, BOARD_COLLIDER_HEIGHT - sz / 2.0))\n        geom.AddScaleOp().Set(Gf.Vec3f(sx, sy, sz))\n        # Hide from rendering via visibility (NOT purpose=guide, which\n        # makes PhysX ignore the prim entirely!)\n        UsdGeom.Imageable(geom.GetPrim()).GetVisibilityAttr().Set(\"invisible\")\n        UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI.Apply(geom.GetPrim())\n        log(f\"  CREATED: {BOARD_COLLIDER_PATH}\")\n        log(f\"    size=({sx}, {sy}, {sz})  top_surface_Z={BOARD_COLLIDER_HEIGHT}\")\n        # Bind friction\n        if friction_mat is not None:\n            bind_api = UsdShade.MaterialBindingAPI.Apply(geom.GetPrim())\n            bind_api.Bind(friction_mat, UsdShade.Tokens.weakerThanDescendants, \"physics\")\n            log(f\"    BOUND → {FRICTION_MAT_PATH} (physics)\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        log(f\"  FAILED to create board collision plane: {e}\")\n        issues.append(f\"Board collision plane: {e}\")\n\n# ---- B. Also add CollisionAPI to Q_ zones (belt-and-suspenders) ----\nfor qpath in QUADRANT_ZONES:\n    qp = stage.GetPrimAtPath(qpath)\n    qname = qpath.split(\"/\")[-1]\n    if not (qp and qp.IsValid()):\n        log(f\"  SKIPPED: {qname} not found at {qpath}\")\n        issues.append(f\"Quadrant {qname} not found\")\n        continue\n\n    try:\n        if not qp.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI):\n            UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI.Apply(qp)\n            log(f\"  ADDED CollisionAPI: {qname}\")\n        else:\n            skipped.append(f\"Collision {qname}\")\n    except Exception as e:\n        log(f\"  FAILED CollisionAPI on {qname}: {e}\")\n        issues.append(f\"CollisionAPI {qname}: {e}\")\n\n    # Bind friction material (physics purpose only — preserve visual colors)\n    if friction_mat is not None:\n        try:\n            bind_api = UsdShade.MaterialBindingAPI.Apply(qp)\n            bind_api.Bind(friction_mat, UsdShade.Tokens.weakerThanDescendants, \"physics\")\n            log(f\"  BOUND: {qname} → {FRICTION_MAT_PATH} (physics)\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            log(f\"  FAILED bind on {qname}: {e}\")\n            issues.append(f\"Bind material to {qname}: {e}\")\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# STEP 6b: JOINT DRIVES — stiffness + damping for position control\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- STEP 6b: JOINT DRIVES ---\")\n\ndef _set_drive(prim, drive_type, stiffness, damping):\n    \"\"\"Find or create a drive on a joint prim and set stiffness/damping.\n    drive_type is 'angular' for revolute joints, 'linear' for prismatic.\n    Returns True if any changes were made.\n    \"\"\"\n    changed = False\n    # The drive is at the 'drive' token under the joint\n    # In USD PhysX, drives are encoded as attributes on the joint prim:\n    #   drive:{drive_type}:physics:stiffness\n    #   drive:{drive_type}:physics:damping\n    #   drive:{drive_type}:physics:type  (\"force\" or \"acceleration\")\n    stiff_name = f\"drive:{drive_type}:physics:stiffness\"\n    damp_name = f\"drive:{drive_type}:physics:damping\"\n    type_name = f\"drive:{drive_type}:physics:type\"\n\n    # Stiffness\n    attr = prim.GetAttribute(stiff_name)\n    if not attr or not attr.IsValid():\n        attr = prim.CreateAttribute(stiff_name, Sdf.ValueTypeNames.Float)\n    cur = attr.Get()\n    if cur is None or abs(float(cur) - stiffness) > 1e-3:\n        attr.Set(stiffness)\n        changed = True\n\n    # Damping\n    attr = prim.GetAttribute(damp_name)\n    if not attr or not attr.IsValid():\n        attr = prim.CreateAttribute(damp_name, Sdf.ValueTypeNames.Float)\n    cur = attr.Get()\n    if cur is None or abs(float(cur) - damping) > 1e-3:\n        attr.Set(damping)\n        changed = True\n\n    # Drive type — use \"force\" (torque-based) which is the standard for\n    # position-controlled articulations\n    attr = prim.GetAttribute(type_name)\n    if not attr or not attr.IsValid():\n        attr = prim.CreateAttribute(type_name, Sdf.ValueTypeNames.Token)\n    if attr.Get() != \"force\":\n        attr.Set(\"force\")\n        changed = True\n\n    return changed\n\n\n# Walk all joint prims under the robot and set drives\ndrive_count = 0\nfor desc in Usd.PrimRange(stage.GetPrimAtPath(ROBOT_PATH)):\n    # Check if this prim has any joint-related type\n    ptype = desc.GetTypeName()\n    if not (\"Joint\" in ptype or desc.IsA(UsdPhysics.Joint)):\n        continue\n\n    joint_name = desc.GetName()\n\n    # Determine if this is an arm joint, gripper joint, or skip\n    stiffness = damping = None\n    for aj in UR5E_ARM_JOINTS:\n        if aj in joint_name:\n            stiffness = ARM_DRIVE_STIFFNESS\n            damping = ARM_DRIVE_DAMPING\n            break\n    if stiffness is None:\n        for gj in GRIPPER_JOINTS:\n            if gj in joint_name:\n                stiffness = GRIPPER_DRIVE_STIFFNESS\n                damping = GRIPPER_DRIVE_DAMPING\n                break\n    if stiffness is None:\n        continue  # unknown joint, skip\n\n    # Determine drive type from joint type\n    drive_type = \"angular\"  # revolute (default for UR5e + robotiq)\n    if \"Prismatic\" in ptype:\n        drive_type = \"linear\"\n\n    did_change = _set_drive(desc, drive_type, stiffness, damping)\n    if did_change:\n        log(f\"  SET: {joint_name}  stiffness={stiffness}  damping={damping}  type=force\")\n        drive_count += 1\n    else:\n        skipped.append(f\"Drive {joint_name}\")\n\nif drive_count == 0:\n    log(\"  All joint drives already configured\")\nelse:\n    log(f\"  Configured {drive_count} joint drive(s)\")\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# STEP 6c: LIGHTING — enforce DomeLight + DistantLight settings\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- STEP 6c: LIGHTING ---\")\n\n# Helper: map config \"type\" string → USD class for Define()\n_LIGHT_CLASS = {\n    \"SphereLight\": UsdLux.SphereLight,\n    \"DomeLight\":   UsdLux.DomeLight,\n    \"DistantLight\": UsdLux.DistantLight,\n}\n\ndef _ensure_xform(path):\n    \"\"\"Create an Xform prim at *path* if it doesn't already exist.\"\"\"\n    p = stage.GetPrimAtPath(path)\n    if p and p.IsValid():\n        return p\n    UsdGeom.Xform.Define(stage, path)\n    log(f\"  CREATED Xform: {path}\")\n    return stage.GetPrimAtPath(path)\n\n\n# Ensure the light-rig container Xforms exist\n_ensure_xform(LIGHT_RIG_PATH)\n_ensure_xform(LIGHT_RIG_LIGHTS_PATH)\n\nfor lcfg in LIGHT_CONFIGS:\n    lpath = lcfg[\"path\"]\n    ltype = lcfg[\"type\"]\n    lname = lpath.rsplit(\"/\", 1)[-1]\n    attrs = lcfg[\"attrs\"]\n    should_create = lcfg.get(\"create\", False)\n\n    prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(lpath)\n    prim_exists = prim and prim.IsValid()\n\n    # --- Create if missing & allowed ---\n    if not prim_exists:\n        if should_create:\n            cls = _LIGHT_CLASS.get(ltype)\n            if cls is None:\n                log(f\"  SKIPPED: unknown light type '{ltype}' for {lpath}\")\n                issues.append(f\"Unknown light type {ltype}\")\n                continue\n            cls.Define(stage, lpath)\n            prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(lpath)\n            log(f\"  CREATED {ltype}: {lpath}\")\n        else:\n            log(f\"  SKIPPED: {lname} not found (create=False)\")\n            continue\n\n    # --- Set attributes ---\n    changed = 0\n    for attr_name, desired in attrs.items():\n        # Visibility is on the imageable, not a light input\n        if attr_name == \"visibility\":\n            imageable = UsdGeom.Imageable(prim)\n            current = imageable.GetVisibilityAttr().Get()\n            if current != desired:\n                imageable.GetVisibilityAttr().Set(desired)\n                log(f\"    SET {attr_name}: {current} → {desired}\")\n                changed += 1\n            continue\n\n        # Boolean attrs in USD require explicit typed creation\n        attr = prim.GetAttribute(attr_name)\n        if not attr or not attr.IsValid():\n            # Create the attribute with correct type\n            if isinstance(desired, bool):\n                attr = prim.CreateAttribute(attr_name, Sdf.ValueTypeNames.Bool)\n            elif isinstance(desired, float):\n                attr = prim.CreateAttribute(attr_name, Sdf.ValueTypeNames.Float)\n            elif isinstance(desired, str):\n                attr = prim.CreateAttribute(attr_name, Sdf.ValueTypeNames.Token)\n            else:\n                attr = prim.CreateAttribute(attr_name, Sdf.ValueTypeNames.Float)\n\n        current = attr.Get()\n        # Compare with tolerance for floats\n        needs_set = False\n        if isinstance(desired, float):\n            needs_set = (current is None) or (abs(float(current) - desired) > 1e-4)\n        elif isinstance(desired, bool):\n            needs_set = (current is None) or (bool(current) != desired)\n        else:\n            needs_set = (current != desired)\n\n        if needs_set:\n            attr.Set(desired)\n            log(f\"    SET {attr_name}: {current} → {desired}\")\n            changed += 1\n\n    # --- Set xform (translate + rotate) ---\n    xform_cfg = LIGHT_XFORMS.get(lpath)\n    if xform_cfg:\n        xformable = UsdGeom.Xformable(prim)\n        # Clear existing xform ops to avoid accumulation on re-runs\n        xformable.ClearXformOpOrder()\n        if \"translate\" in xform_cfg:\n            xformable.AddTranslateOp().Set(xform_cfg[\"translate\"])\n        if \"rotate\" in xform_cfg:\n            r = xform_cfg[\"rotate\"]\n            xformable.AddRotateXYZOp().Set(r)\n        log(f\"    XFORM: translate={xform_cfg.get('translate')}  rotateXYZ={xform_cfg.get('rotate')}\")\n\n    if changed == 0:\n        log(f\"  OK: {lname} — all attributes already correct\")\n        skipped.append(f\"Light {lname}\")\n    else:\n        log(f\"  UPDATED: {lname} — {changed} attribute(s) set\")\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# STEP 7: VERIFY\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n--- STEP 7: VERIFICATION ---\")\nlog(\"\")\n\n# Cube — physics\ncube_ok = False\nif cube_prim and cube_prim.IsValid():\n    has_rb = cube_prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.RigidBodyAPI)\n    has_col = cube_prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI)\n    mass_api = UsdPhysics.MassAPI(cube_prim) if cube_prim.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.MassAPI) else None\n    m = mass_api.GetMassAttr().Get() if mass_api else None\n    cube_ok = (has_rb and has_col and m is not None and abs(m - CUBE_MASS_KG) < 1e-6)\n    rb_s = \"✓\" if has_rb else \"✗\"\n    col_s = \"✓\" if has_col else \"✗\"\n    mass_s = \"✓\" if (m is not None and abs(m - CUBE_MASS_KG) < 1e-6) else \"✗\"\n    log(f\"  {rb_s} Cube RigidBody  {col_s} Cube Collision  {mass_s} mass={m} (want {CUBE_MASS_KG})\")\n    # Check purpose isn't \"guide\"\n    purpose = UsdGeom.Imageable(cube_prim).GetPurposeAttr().Get()\n    if purpose == \"guide\":\n        log(f\"  ⚠ Cube purpose='guide' — PhysX will IGNORE it!\")\n\n# Colliders — check they exist AND aren't purpose=\"guide\"\nfor link_name, _, _ in COLLIDER_CONFIGS:\n    found = False\n    for cpath in [f\"{ROBOT_PATH}/{link_name}/collisions/pad_collider\",\n                  f\"{ROBOT_PATH}/{link_name}/pad_collider\"]:\n        p = stage.GetPrimAtPath(cpath)\n        if p and p.IsValid() and p.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI):\n            purpose = UsdGeom.Imageable(p).GetPurposeAttr().Get()\n            if purpose == \"guide\":\n                log(f\"  ⚠ Collider {cpath} has purpose='guide' — PhysX ignores it!\")\n            else:\n                log(f\"  ✓ Collider: {cpath}\")\n            found = True\n            break\n    if not found:\n        log(f\"  ✗ Collider MISSING for {link_name}\")\n\n# Instancing\nrobot_prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(ROBOT_PATH)\nif robot_prim and robot_prim.IsValid():\n    still_instanced = robot_prim.IsInstanceable()\n    status = \"✓\" if not still_instanced else \"✗\"\n    log(f\"  {status} Robot instanceable = {still_instanced} (want False)\")\n\n# Friction material\nmat_prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(FRICTION_MAT_PATH)\nif mat_prim and mat_prim.IsValid():\n    log(f\"  ✓ Friction material exists at {FRICTION_MAT_PATH}\")\nelse:\n    log(f\"  ✗ Friction material MISSING at {FRICTION_MAT_PATH}\")\n\n# QuadrantBoard — collision plane\ncol_p = stage.GetPrimAtPath(BOARD_COLLIDER_PATH)\nif col_p and col_p.IsValid() and col_p.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI):\n    log(f\"  ✓ Board collision plane: {BOARD_COLLIDER_PATH}\")\nelse:\n    log(f\"  ✗ Board collision plane MISSING at {BOARD_COLLIDER_PATH}\")\n\n# QuadrantBoard — Q_ zones (secondary)\nfor qpath in QUADRANT_ZONES:\n    qp = stage.GetPrimAtPath(qpath)\n    qname = qpath.split(\"/\")[-1]\n    if qp and qp.IsValid():\n        has_col = qp.HasAPI(UsdPhysics.CollisionAPI)\n        # Check friction binding\n        has_friction = False\n        try:\n            bind_api = UsdShade.MaterialBindingAPI(qp)\n            mat, _ = bind_api.ComputeBoundMaterial(\"physics\")\n            if mat and mat.GetPath() == FRICTION_MAT_PATH:\n                has_friction = True\n        except Exception:\n            pass\n        col_status = \"✓\" if has_col else \"✗\"\n        fric_status = \"✓\" if has_friction else \"✗\"\n        log(f\"  {col_status} {qname} collision  {fric_status} friction\")\n    else:\n        log(f\"  ✗ {qname} NOT FOUND\")\n\n# Lights\nfor lcfg in LIGHT_CONFIGS:\n    lpath = lcfg[\"path\"]\n    lname = lpath.rsplit(\"/\", 1)[-1]\n    prim = stage.GetPrimAtPath(lpath)\n    if not (prim and prim.IsValid()):\n        if lcfg.get(\"create\", False):\n            log(f\"  ✗ Light MISSING: {lname}\")\n        else:\n            log(f\"  — Light {lname}: not in scene (create=False, OK)\")\n        continue\n    # Spot-check a key attribute per light\n    attrs = lcfg[\"attrs\"]\n    all_ok = True\n    for attr_name, desired in attrs.items():\n        if attr_name == \"visibility\":\n            actual = UsdGeom.Imageable(prim).GetVisibilityAttr().Get()\n        else:\n            a = prim.GetAttribute(attr_name)\n            actual = a.Get() if (a and a.IsValid()) else None\n        match = False\n        if isinstance(desired, float) and actual is not None:\n            match = abs(float(actual) - desired) < 1e-4\n        elif isinstance(desired, bool) and actual is not None:\n            match = bool(actual) == desired\n        else:\n            match = (actual == desired)\n        if not match:\n            log(f\"  ✗ {lname}.{attr_name} = {actual} (want {desired})\")\n            all_ok = False\n    if all_ok:\n        log(f\"  ✓ Light {lname} — all attributes correct\")\n\n# Joint drives\nall_joints = [(j, ARM_DRIVE_STIFFNESS, ARM_DRIVE_DAMPING) for j in UR5E_ARM_JOINTS] + \\\n             [(j, GRIPPER_DRIVE_STIFFNESS, GRIPPER_DRIVE_DAMPING) for j in GRIPPER_JOINTS]\nfor jname, want_stiff, want_damp in all_joints:\n    found_joint = False\n    for desc in Usd.PrimRange(stage.GetPrimAtPath(ROBOT_PATH)):\n        if jname in desc.GetName() and \"Joint\" in desc.GetTypeName():\n            found_joint = True\n            drive_type = \"linear\" if \"Prismatic\" in desc.GetTypeName() else \"angular\"\n            s_attr = desc.GetAttribute(f\"drive:{drive_type}:physics:stiffness\")\n            d_attr = desc.GetAttribute(f\"drive:{drive_type}:physics:damping\")\n            s_val = s_attr.Get() if (s_attr and s_attr.IsValid()) else None\n            d_val = d_attr.Get() if (d_attr and d_attr.IsValid()) else None\n            s_ok = s_val is not None and abs(float(s_val) - want_stiff) < 1\n            d_ok = d_val is not None and abs(float(d_val) - want_damp) < 1\n            if s_ok and d_ok:\n                log(f\"  ✓ Drive {jname} stiff={s_val} damp={d_val}\")\n            else:\n                log(f\"  ✗ Drive {jname} stiff={s_val}(want {want_stiff}) damp={d_val}(want {want_damp})\")\n            break\n    if not found_joint:\n        log(f\"  — Drive {jname}: joint not found (may use different name)\")\n\n\n# ============================================================\n# SUMMARY\n# ============================================================\nlog(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 60)\nif not issues:\n    log(\"ALL DONE — no issues detected\")\nelse:\n    log(f\"DONE WITH {len(issues)} ISSUE(S):\")\n    for issue in issues:\n        log(f\"  ⚠ {issue}\")\n\nif skipped:\n    log(f\"\\nAlready done (skipped): {', '.join(skipped)}\")\n\nlog(\"\")\nlog(\"IMPORTANT REMINDERS:\")\nlog(\"  • Save the USD scene after running this script (File → Save)\")\nlog(\"  • If cube is red from a previous script, fix visually:\")\nlog(\"    Select /Test_Cube → Property → Material → reassign original material\")\nlog(\"=\" * 60)\n\nsave_report()\n",
      "tags": [
        "learning",
        "sim2sim",
        "imitation"
      ],
