    {
      "id": "ktt9lk5w",
      "title": "Understanding the ACT policy from Scratch",
      "content": "\n\n\n- Problems with naive CVAE based architectures:\n  - Componding Problems: one wrong action influences all the actions that is coming thereafter\n    - Intresting way to solve this was by using the concept of chunking - predicting multiple steps into the future which in turn reduces the drifts that could be \n      introduced from seperate predictions per step.\n    - How do we decide the optimal chunck size:\n      - Too many: Inference becomes slow and this in turn induces jerkiness",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": null,
