      "title": "2026-05-25 — Daily",
      "content": "# Top 3\n- Finish all the pending tasks\n- List out all the PHD openings \n- Research about foundation models and VLM for scene understanding\n- Complete at least 3 pending NLM notebooks\n- Complete Mimic Video\n\n## Tasks\n\n## Journal\n\n## Wins\n\n\n\n# Skills to have a healthy relationship\n- Premarital Education:\n  - No amount of premarital education can make up for a bad partner choice\n- 3 important things in a healthy relationship\n  - Genuinely knowing what you want from a relationship or partner\n  - Selecting the right person\n  - Developing and using skills right from the begining\n\n- Skills based model of relationship\n  - Romantic competence is the ability to function adaptively across all areas or all aspects of the relationship process\n  - Insight\n    - Insight is about awarness, understanding and learning \n      - It gives a better idea of who you are, what you need, what you want and why you do the things you do.\n      - It helps us evaluate the negative and positive consequences of our behaviour\n      - Also helps us understand what is really right for you in a relationship\n  - Mutuality\n    - Both people have needs and both sets of needs matter\n    - It helps to convey your need in a clear and direct fashion that increases the likelyhood for them to get met\n - Emotion Regulation\n    - Its about regulating our feelings in response to things that happen in a relationship\n    - It helps to stay and keep things happening in a relation to perspective\n    - It helps to tolerate uncomfortable feelinsg and helps to navigate\n    - It helps to maintain self respect",
