    {
      "id": "lwvh19v2",
      "title": "2026-05-30 — Daily",
      "content": "# Top 3\n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n- [ ] \n\n## Tasks\n\n## Journal\n\n## Wins\n\n\n# The future of Humanoids\n    - The first era of robotics started in 60s\n    - The second era started in the 2000s - mobile robots in the warehouses\n- By 2050, the market for humanoid is 2x compared to automobiles\n- Perks of Embodied AI\n  - Solve the problem of capacity - 90% work in industry and 2% in agriculture\n  - Solve the problem of capability - Things that were not probable in the past would become probable because we are doing a lot of things which we did not know how to do earlier, but we could only speculate and imagine what that would be.\n- Embodied AI - Cognition + Skills + Coordination + Physics\n- Reasons why the progress in robotics is slow:\n  - Chaos: Everyones home is different any given day\n  - Cost: The robots have to be capable and cost effective at the same time\n  - Safety: No excuse on the safety aspect hence buiding that kind of trust takes time\n- 3Ds - Dull, Dirty and Dangeorus\n\nSafety first approach:\n    - Pioneering an approach to safety - Workcell approach - Safety-centered isolation - Sensors based thirdy party certified safe behaviours ",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": "2026-05-30",
      "type": "daily",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2026-05-30T19:38:30.887Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-05-31T00:34:30.344Z",
