    {
      "id": "vsvsf1g2",
      "title": "📥 Inbox",
      "content": "# 📥 Research Inbox\n\n**How it works:** Press **Alt+I** anywhere in UltraNote to capture a paper, link, or idea here in one keystroke. Don't read it now — just capture. Every Friday, triage this list (promote into a paper note or delete).\n\n**Shortcuts:**\n- **Alt+I** → capture to this inbox\n- **Alt+P** → new structured paper note\n- **Alt+M** → new / open a topic map (create one whenever a thread starts repeating)\n\n## Captures\n- [ ] [2026-06-26 01:53] Lectures | Introduction to Robot Learning — https://16-831-s24.github.io/lectures/\n- [ ] [2026-06-26 01:47] GitHub - telekinesis-ai/telekinesis-examples: Telekinesis Agentic Skill Library: build AI-powered Computer Vision, Robotics and Physical AI applications. · GitHub — https://github.com/telekinesis-ai/telekinesis-examples\n- [ ] [2026-06-26 01:41] Robot Self-Improvement via Human-Video Dynamics Models — https://ethz-mrl.github.io/robot-self-improvement-website/\n- [ ] [2026-06-25 03:32] Introducing Odyssey-2 Max: Scaled World Simulation — https://odyssey.ml/introducing-odyssey-2-max\n- [ ] [2026-06-25 03:02] Pretrained to Imagine, Fine-Tuned to Act: The Rise of World-Action Models | NVIDIA Technical Blog — https://developer.nvidia.com/blog/pretrained-to-imagine-fine-tuned-to-act-the-rise-of-world-action-models/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\n- [ ] [2026-06-25 03:00] What 1,228 Vision-Language-Action Papers Say About the Robot Data Problem | Label Studio — https://labelstud.io/blog/vla-robot-data-problem/?utm_source=chatgpt.com\n- [ ] [2026-06-25 02:15] VLA-REPLICA: A Low-Cost, Reproducible Benchmark for Real-World Evaluation of Vision-Language-Action Models — https://arxiv.org/html/2605.20774v1?utm_source=chatgpt.com\n- [ ] [2026-06-25 01:54] Physical AI with World Foundation Models | NVIDIA Cosmos — https://www.nvidia.com/en-us/ai/cosmos/?ncid=pa-srch-goog-505559&_bt=810417246181&_bk=cosmos%203&_bm=p&_bn=g&_bg=198383530073&gad_source=1&gad_campaignid=23888110705&gbraid=0AAAAAD4XAoF2Ye10m6_IkuzirDgjPTB0G&gclid=CjwKCAjwgO7RBhBKEiwAZNP85khipRZh2jnC_BtZtpkCBBCsj4KUZjCP7xcz6blzSC9QljQgABxZQRoCf1IQAvD_BwE\n<!--trashed:2026-06-24T04:29:02.530Z--> - [ ] [2026-06-24 04:28] — https://arxiv.org/pdf/2502.04307\n- [ ] [2026-06-23 23:49] microsoft/SkillOpt: SkillOpt is a text-space optimizer that trains reusable natural-language skills for frozen LLM agents through trajectory-driven edits, validation-gated updates, and deployable best_skill.md artifacts. — https://github.com/microsoft/SkillOpt\n- [ ] [2026-06-23 17:02] — https://arxiv.org/pdf/2606.23444\n- [ ] [2026-06-22 21:17] https://www.linkedin.com/safety/go/?url=https://lnkd.in/gSPJPKyh\n- [ ] [2026-06-22 21:16] https://www.linkedin.com/safety/go/?url=https://lnkd.in/d6pQJY2P\n- [ ] [2026-06-22 21:15] https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.18610\n- [ ] [2026-06-22 21:14] https://www.linkedin.com/safety/go/?url=https://lnkd.in/gt6t5S7w\n- [ ] [2026-06-22 19:29] https://www.linkedin.com/safety/go/?url=https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLW_xDnYtBZJkLD5rXCvLw44ZeSD3BKqFf\n- [ ] [2026-06-22 17:19] DoorMan - NVIDIA GEAR Lab — https://doorman-humanoid.github.io/\n- [ ] [2026-06-22 16:48] [2603.09971] TiPToP: A Modular Open-Vocabulary Planning System for Robotic Manipulation — https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.09971\n- [ ] [2026-06-22 06:13] AshrafGalibShaik/Difotrain: An embodiment-agnostic framework for training Vision-Language-Action (VLA) models from the real world — https://github.com/AshrafGalibShaik/Difotrain\n- [ ] [2026-06-22 01:42] PolarDepth: Polarization-Guided Monocular Depth for Visual Odometry | IEEE Journals & Magazine | IEEE Xplore — https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/abstract/document/11488501\n- [ ] [2026-06-21 20:25] FACTR 2 — https://jasonjzliu.com/factr2/\n- [ ] [2026-06-21 02:33] Source: Threads https://share.google/nyZhpeUYGTw2HjmgG\n- [ ] [2026-06-21 01:16] Scalable Behavior Cloning with Open Data, Training, and Evaluation — https://abc.bot/\n- [ ] [2026-06-20 22:33] (3846) Alpamayo 2 Super: The Open Reasoning Model for