      "id": "aanuao5h",
      "title": "🔁 Weekly Triage Ritual",
      "content": "# 🔁 Weekly Triage Ritual (Fridays, 30 min)\n\nA task auto-appears every Friday on the Today page. The ritual:\n\n1. **Open 📥 Inbox.** For each item, decide: *Promote*, *Skim later*, or *Delete*.\n2. **Promote** → press **Alt+P**, paste the title, fill the template. Tag with relevant topic.\n3. **Skim later** → keep in inbox but prepend \"later: \" — bumps for next week.\n4. **Delete** → just remove the line. Ruthless is good.\n5. **Update topic maps** — if a paper materially changes the field, add 1–2 lines to the right \"🗺️ Topic Map\".\n6. **Close the loop** — anything that became a TODO gets added as a task with a due date.\n\n**Why this works:** the inbox stays small, the topic maps stay living, and at the end of every month the monthly synthesis writes itself from the deltas in the topic maps.\n",
      "tags": [
        "research",
        "ritual",
        "system"
      ],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "page",
      "pinned": false,
