    {
      "id": "84gqitt9",
      "title": "SimTOOLReal",
      "content": "# SimTOOLReal - An object centric policy for Zero-Shot Dexterous Tool Manipulation\n\n**Added:** 2026-05-31  **Status:** #status/skim\n**Tags:** #paper\n\n## Metadata\n- **Authors:** Kushal Kedia, Tyler Lum, Karen Liu , Jeannette Bohg\n- **Venue / Year:** 2026\n- **Link:**\n- **Code:**\n- **DOI / arXiv id:**\n\n## TL;DR (3 lines, in your own words)\n-\n\n## Problem\n- Contact rich teleoperation data are difficult to collect using teleoepration especially with teleop\n    - Teleop limits the ability of the robots \n- Data mismatch between sim and real - Mostly handled with domain randomization with physics and visual\n- Most dextorous task to be successful in teh sim2real paradigm requries task specific reward tuning and environment design - task specific engineering was required\n- \n\n## Method\n-  Unify Manipulations as Goal Pose - Reaching - Continuos and repetative update of goal poses that the robot has to hit with the tool until the task is done \n    - Input to the policy is \n        - the propriception of the robot -\n        -  current object pose and the goal target pose\n        - grasp bounding box     \n```mermaid\nflowchart LR\n  Inputs --> LSTM_Policy --> Joint_Position_Target\n```\n- Absoluet action space for the hand and delta action space for the arm(EMA Filter for smoothening)\n- Training is done with teh unified objective of moving random objects to random goals\n- During inference in real the policy is made to track object goals from human video\n\n## Challenges\n- Pose estimation for small objects\n- Heavy objects were hard to be kept in control within the hands\n\n## Results\n-  High dof tool manipulation with 1x speed and 60hz policy control\n-  Single policy and zero shot on novel tools and tasks\n-  Benchmarks on which the testing was done -\n    - Fixed Grasp(Uses closed loop reactive policy to achieve fixed grasp) - Uses arm movement to achieve in hand rotation instead of the hand itself - **FAILS TO CAPTURE TOOL ROTATION**\n    - Kinematic Retargeting to copy human hand movements of the video\n**FAILS TO CAPTURE BOTH GRASP AND TOOL ROTATION**\n-  Recovery from failures was descent\n\n## My take (so what? does it change anything I do?)\n- I would love to dissassociate the policy's objective from being too specific about a handling a object to making the policy work for a more general goal - like grasp object as long the best grasp is available or track object given the goal pose is available\n\n## Connections\n- Relevant to topic map: [[🗺️ Topic Map — Video Action Models ]]\n\n## Quotes / snippets worth keeping\n> Make Simulation General and Unified \n> Sim policies often do just enough to get the task done than generalize\n\n## Follow-ups\n- [ ] Test the codebase \n- [ ] Understand how SAM3D can be incorporated \n",
      "tags": [
        "paper",
        "research"
      ],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "page",
      "pinned": false,
      "notebookId": "wvskhat9",
