      "id": "olilxh8i",
      "title": "2026-06-07 — Daily",
      "content": "# Top 3\n- [ ] Complete the VFS application form and registration\n- [ ] Complete the I983 form\n- [ ] Create a solid plan for tomorrow - VAM\n\n## Tasks\n\n## Journal\n\n## Wins\n\n# Why your best ideas usually start as bad ones?\n- The mistake is the journey\n\n# Between stimulus and response there is a space!\n- Numerous strategies to regulate emotions-\n    - Process Model\n        - Enter a situation - Real or Imagined\n        - Evaluate the situation - Evaluate or Appraise the situation as whether it helps or hinders our goal\n        - Emotional Response - Leads to a set of changes in how we feel, think and behave\n    - The above are the 3 stages into which one could intervene and make changes to turn things in your favor\n    - No situation is inherently bad or good but just helpful or unhelpful depending on the situation",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": "2026-06-07",
      "type": "daily",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2026-06-07T15:16:00.395Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-07T22:13:41.411Z",
      "attachments": [],
      "links": [],
      "deletedAt": null,
      "journal": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "mkwupzkt",
      "title": "Building Large Language Models",
      "content": "What matter when training LLM\n\n- Architecture \n- Data\n- Training algorithm or loss\n- Evaluation\n- Systems\n\n> most of accademia focuses on architecture and training loss while most relevant is data evaluation and systems \n\nTokenizer:\n- More general than words\n- Shorter sequences than with characters\n**tokens as common subsequences**\nByte Pair Encoding(BPE)\n- Take large corpus of text\n- Start with one token per character\n- Merge common pairs of tokens into a token\n- Repeat until desired vocab size or all merged\n\n_**punctuations are language specific and taken care of in ways that tokenizer training is optimized - in english any token before or after a space is ignored from the process of being considered for tokenization**_\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "note",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2026-06-07T22:13:42.614Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-13T21:30:45.198Z",
      "attachments": [],
      "links": [],
      "status": "followup"
    },
