      "id": "dzzx7sah",
      "title": "Game Theory Tactics",
      "content": "- Jon Von Neumann & Oskar Morgenstern wrote the book Theory of Games\n- Game Theory - Study of Decision Making under conditions of uncertainity over time\n    - Build to understand how people behaved in certain scenarios\n- One thing that game theory has always proven is that alot of things or interactions which we believed to be zero sum or competetive is not as competetive as they seem.\n- Life at any point is about dealing with uncertainity and possibilities.\n- Sunk cost fallacy - You have to have the mindset to forget about the sunk cost and always look for newer opportunities if it means they produce better outcomes\n- Best strategy in zero sum games to pursue when up against sophiticated opponents is to adopt the strategy that minimizes your maximum loss. - MiniMax Strategy - Adopt the strategy that minimizes your maximum loss - what is the worst case scenario that could put you in maximum loss and work on ways to minimize that loss ",
      "tags": [],
