    {
      "id": "afqk66dh",
      "title": "Alpamayo 2 ",
      "content": "Key Takeaways\n- Reasoning is the New Frontier: The industry is moving beyond simple trajectory generation. The goal is now for the model to \"reason, plan, and act\" across the full stack. This involves producing Chain-of-Causation (CoC) traces—where the model explains its driving logic—alongside its actions.\n\n- Closed-Loop is Mandatory: Open-loop training (evaluating against fixed datasets) is insufficient. Effective models must now be trained in closed-loop simulation (like NVIDIA AlpaGym), where the model’s actions directly influence the environment it perceives, exposing compounding errors and edge cases.\n\n- Physical AI Agentic Workflows: Developing AVs is increasingly being treated as a task for AI Agents. Rather than manual data pipeline management, researchers are now using \"Physical AI Agent Skills\" to automate scenario generation, neural scene reconstruction, and reinforcement learning loops.\n\n\n\n- [ ] Familiarize with the Stack: Study how NVIDIA DRIVE Hyperion and Drive AGX Thor integrate these models into vehicles.\n- [ ] Focus on Evaluation: Research \"Counterfactual Testing\" in VLA models. This is currently one of the most critical areas for validating that reasoning models are safe for deployment.\n- [ ] Hands-on: Explore the Open X-Embodiment datasets to understand the data-scale requirements for training general-purpose policies.",
      "tags": [],
      "projectId": null,
      "dateIndex": null,
      "type": "note",
      "pinned": false,
      "createdAt": "2026-06-23T00:32:16.681Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-06-23T01:46:16.380Z",
      "attachments": [],
      "links": [],
      "status": null
