    {
      "id": "ncb4cpdf",
      "title": "Automated Data Collection Pipeline",
      "status": "DONE",
      "due": "2026-06-01",
      "noteId": "ibu8gl3n",
      "projectId": "c7szb5bi",
      "priority": "high",
      "description": "The idea is to orchestrate a data collection pipeline using Behaviour Tree\n  - First in simulation - Isaacsim\n  - Then implement the same in realrobot\n\nPnP Inspiration based work from https://github.com/JuoTungChen/ROS2_pick_and_place_UR5?tab=readme-ov-file\nros2 launch ur_bringup ur_control.launch.py \\\n  ur_type:=ur5e \\\n  robot_ip:=192.168.0.10 \\\n  use_fake_hardware:=true \\\n  description_package:=ur5_gripper_description \\\n  description_file:=ur5_robotiq85_gripper.urdf.xacro \\\n  runtime_config_package:=ur_robot_driver \\\n  controllers_file:=ur_controllers.yaml \\\n  initial_joint_controller:=joint_trajectory_controller \\\n  launch_gripper_controller:=true \\\n  activate_gripper_controller:=true\n\nros2 launch ur5_gripper_moveit_config ur5_gripper_moveit.launch.py \\\n  launch_controllers:=false use_fake_hardware:=true launch_servo:=true launch_rviz:=true\n\n\nros2 control load_controller gripper_position_controller\n\n# or single line:\nros2 control load_controller --set-state active gripper_position_controller\nros2 control load_controller gripper_position_controller\nros2 control set_controller_state gripper_position_controller active\n\nros2 action send_goal /gripper_position_controller/gripper_cmd control_msgs/action/GripperCommand \\\n  \"{command: {position: 0.0, max_effort: 50.0}}\"\n\n\n\n\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n ros2 run ur_client_library start_ursim.sh -m ur5e\n\n\n\nros2 launch ur_moveit_config ur_moveit.launch.py ur_type:=ur5e launch_rviz:=true\n\n\nCurrent Status and TODOS:\n1. The work inspired from the pick and place package is successfully translated to Humble\n2. All the package specific actions seems to be working well for UR5 + Robotiq config\n3. Finetune the BT behaviour and get it to work with 3 clean pnp poses\n  - Ensure the GUI is working clean\n  - Integrate the ROSBAG recording services\n  - Finally for the meeting have a vide recording of the pick and place action happening with rosbag recording then replay the rosbag and show the recorded sample\n\nReference Package:\nhttps://github.com/JuoTungChen/ROS2_pick_and_place_UR5?tab=readme-ov-file\n\n\n",
